title: banana bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar; beat well.
Add beaten eggs and mashed bananas.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to first mixture with milk and vanilla.
Beat well.	Add nuts and pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Crush bananas.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix soda and flour together and add to first mixture.
Grease pan and sprinkle flour on bottom.
Add melted butter and bake at 350°.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs, and cook.
Let cool.
Roll into balls.
Dip in eggs and roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry until brown.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in shallow, greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg and granulated sugar.
Add water.
Combine brown sugar and flour.
Cut in butter very fine.
Spread over apples. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes.
Cut in squares for serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crown jewel patties
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg.
Add mayonnaise, onion, oil, salt, pepper and carrots; mix well.
Add the bread crumbs and mix thoroughly (if mixture is too wet to handle, add more crumbs). Shape into 10 to 12 patties; coat with cornflakes.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: microwave pie crust
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and press into a buttered 9 inch round baking dish.
Microwave at high for 1 1/2 minutes or until firm, rotating dish after 1 minute.
Yield: one 9 inch pie shell.

title: memphis roasted shrimp
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place cold shrimp in roasting pan.
Dot with entire pound of butter.
Squeeze lemons over shrimp, then drop lemons into pan.
Pour dressing over contents of pan.
Top with pepper.
Bake 25 minutes uncovered, turn mixture completely and continue to cook 20 more minutes.
Serve with French bread for dipping in liquid from pan.

title: one pan cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in 11 x 7-inch pan.
Add milk, Bisquick and sugar; stir until smooth.
Drop spoonfuls of filling over batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash, core and slice tomatoes in 1/3-inch slices.
Do not peel.
Dip each slice in flour, season to taste with salt and pepper and fry until golden in hot oil.
Drain on paper toweling, then serve hot with butter.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve jello in water. Stir in strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts. Pour half of the mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2 dish. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until set. Set the remaining jello mixture aside. Combine the sour cream, sugar and vanilla; mix well. Spread over the chilled jello. Spoon remaining jello mixture over top. Chill overnight. Yield: 12 to 15 servings.

title: chili stuffed potatoes
directions: Pierce potatoes; cook in microwave on High for 16 minutes or until soft.
In a large skillet, brown meat and drain.
Stir in corn, tomatoes, ketchup, pepper and chili powder.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Slit potatoes; spoon 1 cup meat mixture over each potato.
Garnish with sour cream, grated Cheddar cheese and green onions, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine beans, peas and pimentos.
Add chopped pepper, onion and celery.
Mix together sugar, vinegar and oil and pour over vegetables and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: fruit salad sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Whisk in water, orange juice and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil whisking constantly over medium heat for one minute.
Pour mixture over prepared fruit tossing gently to coat.
Cover and chill.

title: lemon basil chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix salad dressing, juice, honey and basil.
Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread with salad dressing mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until cooked through. Makes 4 servings.

title: sugar crisp peanuts
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar and water and bring to a boil to dissolve sugar.
Add raw peanuts and boil over medium heat until sugar crystalizes and no syrup is left.
Stir while boiling to evenly coat peanuts.

title: jelly cookies
directions: Take good teaspoon of dough.
Roll in white sugar.
Press finger in top and fill with jelly.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: my uncle's wild rice pilaf
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan.
Add onions, cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Simmering time may vary due to type of pan and amount of broth used.
Adjust recipe as needed.
(If you have a rice cooker, coat bottom of pan with nonstick vegetable spray, add all ingredients and push the cook button!)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Mix sour cream, dill weed and dressing mix.
Add cucumber and onion; refrigerate until firm.
Serve with fresh vegetables or Hawaiian bread.

title: party ham casserole
directions: Mix butter, flour and milk; stir constantly until thickened. Add cheese; cook slowly until melted.
Arrange potatoes in greased casserole; cover with beans.
Add ham, then pour sauce on top. Melt 2 tablespoons butter and mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan cheese treats
directions: Whip together Cheddar cheese and sour cream.
Shape scant tablespoon to form 16 cheese balls.
Press each ball between 2 pecan halves and chill.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and pour into greased casserole dish.
Mix onion, soup and sour cream.
Pour this mixture on vegetables.
Add cheese.
Cover with crackers.
Add margarine.
Add almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, cheese, onion, soup and mayonnaise together.
Put into 7 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with crushed crackers and dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: rosa's punch
directions: Chill ingredients.
Mix in punch bowl, adding 7-Up last.
Add drops of food coloring to suit occasion, as desired.
Stir float block of ice.
Add orange and lemon slices.

title: frito casserole
directions: Cook ground meat until done; drain.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish as follows:
meat, Fritos, onions, cheese and sauce until you have used all.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook chicken; take off the bone, then add back to broth.
Add vegetables (except bean sprouts) and cook until tender.
Then add bean sprouts.
Use the cornstarch for thickening the last 3 or 4 minutes.
Use over rice or noodles.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and beat.
Add oil, water and pumpkin. Add flour mixture.
Add 1 cup ground nuts.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes in 3 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Can add 1/2 teaspoon lemon or orange flavoring.

title: french beef stew
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving, in large Dutch oven over medium heat, fry bacon until crisp.
Push to side of pan.
Add meat and brown.
Stir in 1 cup water, wine, bouillon cube, garlic, onion, salt, thyme and orange peel.
Reduce heat to low and cover. Simmer for 2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: razorback corn bread
directions: Brown sausage and save 2 to 3 tablespoons grease; set aside. Combine dry ingredients.
Add all wet ingredients.
Add sausage and reserved grease.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beer batter
directions: Pour beer into a bowl; add flour.
Mixture will foam.
Stir in salt, paprika and baking powder.
If using to fry fruit, you may want to use cinnamon or nutmeg instead of paprika.
Mixture will thicken as it stands.
Make this at least 1 hour before using.
It will keep in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days.
Yield: about 2 1/2 cups batter.
Preparation time: 1 minute.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, egg and orange juice.
Stir in orange rind.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Add to first mixture; then add cranberries and nuts.
Just stir enough to moisten ingredients.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: basic cookie mix
directions: Mix flour, dry milk and sift together 2 times.
Soften shortening, gradually add sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend using the low speed on mixer until coarse like corn meal.
Store in large canister at room temperature.
Keeps for several weeks.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon, together.
Put in baking dish.
Lay strips of bacon on top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix together and pour over crackers.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Stir in crackers.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes; stir halfway through.
Store in plastic bag.
Put any loose seasoning in with crackers.
Time:
20 minutes.

title: creamy lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Chill until slightly thickened, then whip Jell-O, sugar, vanilla and softened cream cheese together.
Clean beaters off, then whip Pet milk until it is real stiff.
Combine Jell-O mixture, whipped milk, pineapple, nuts and cherries.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch Tupperware flat pan. Chill and cut into squares or serve in a large bowl.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Pour melted margarine into a
9 x 13 inch pan. Mix all ingredients together in bowl. Pour batter into pan and bake at 375° until lightly browned on top.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook beef until tender, in a large pot.
Lower to medium heat. Add carrots, celery, garlic, onion and potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: spinach squares
directions: Put butter in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Melt in oven; remove. In large bowl, beat eggs well. Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder; mix well. Add cheese, spinach and onion; mix well. Spoon into baking dish and level off. Bake 35 minutes in preheated oven (350°). Cool for 45 minutes, then cut into bite size squares. Bon appetit!

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook ground beef.
Drain real well.
Add all the ingredients. Cook on low heat for about 6 to 7 hours.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients, except hash browns.
Spread hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cheese-soup mixture over the top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Process in food processor to make a spread.

title: potato and ham casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Layer potatoes (sliced), salt and pepper, onions and ham.
Pour 1/2 cup milk mixed with cream of mushroom soup over layers.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, covered.
Remove lid and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in a salad bowl.
Let set in refrigerator overnight or at least 6 hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle with grated cheese and bacon bits.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put rice in water with salt.
Cook 7 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add milk, butter and vanilla.
Simmer slowly 1/2 hour, covered lightly.
Add sugar and raisins.
Cook slowly 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Refrigerate until thickened.

title: taco salad
directions: On a cookie sheet, layer shredded lettuce, cheese and tomatoes, saving enough lettuce, tomatoes and cheese to sprinkle over top of salad.
Pour Ortega sauce over lettuce, tomato and cheese layer.
Spread bean mix evenly over the sauce.
Sprinkle with lettuce, cheese and tomatoes. Refrigerate until serving time. Serve with nachos.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries; mix with marshmallows and sugar.
Cover; chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, nuts and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Serve in large bowl or individual lettuce cups. Garnish with clusters of green grapes and fresh cranberries. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar
and
butter;
add
eggs, one at a time and beat. Add
milk and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda together.
Add
flour.
Mix
nuts and bananas all at once and stir
until
mixed.
Pour
into greased loaf pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: libby's famous pumpkin pie
directions: Mix filling in order given.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center of pie filling comes out clean.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, milk and sugar.
Melt margarine in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour mixture into melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Spoon pie filling in next.
Do not stir. Cook approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: orange smoothee(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Pour the milk in a large bowl.
Add the other ingredients. Using a hand eggbeater, mix well until the mixture is foamy.
Serve at once.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt, sifted together.
Then add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Mix well and bake in an oblong or tube pan for 1 hour or until done.

title: spiced carrots
directions: Clean and slice carrots.
Place with butter in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 10 minutes.
Stir dish 3 times during cycle.
Add orange sections, salt and nutmeg.
Cook, covered, 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all soups, salsa, milk and onion.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer tortillas, chicken and salsa mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Refrigerate 24 hours before baking at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add egg, oil and vanilla and mix. Add gradually the flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Then add last 3 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 75 cookies.

title: best all-american brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt the 1/2 pound butter and let cool.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and vanilla until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar until blended and then beat in butter.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake until brownies begin to pull away from the sides of pan, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool before cutting into squares.
Makes 24.

title: garlic-lemon chicken
directions: Boil chicken until cooked.
Baste with a mixture of melted butter, lemon and diced garlic cloves.
Place in broiler until chicken begins to brown.
Baste again.
After
few minutes, turn over and repeat until browned on both sides.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli squares
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Grind broccoli in food processor/blender.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter until onions are limp.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cut bacon into squares and brown.
Pour off all fat except 1 tablespoon.
Add and brown medium, finely diced onion, garlic and ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on slow flame for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: eggplant parmigian
directions: Saute in butter, onions, garlic and beef until beef is no longer red.
Add tomato paste, salt, pepper, brown sugar and herbs.
Add 1 cup water and simmer uncovered 10 or 20 minutes.
Do not peel eggplant, cut crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Make equal amount Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Makes one cup. Dip eggplant in beaten eggs; coat well.
Saute in oil golden brown crisp.
Butter baking dish 1/2 eggplant slices.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Top with Mozzarella.
Sauce.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven, uncovered.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add ice cream by spoonfuls. Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in Cool Whip and add fruit. Pour into 1 baked and cooled pie crust.
Chill about three hours before serving.

title: cherry delight cake
directions: Cook all ingredients at 350° until done except whipped cream. Top with whipped cream.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak up; flour and cook in cooking oil until tender.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and onion; saute until tender, then add tomato soup and sour cream.
Cook another 10 to 15 minutes.
Add water as needed.
Serve over hot rice.

title: eggplant, corn and cheese casserole
directions: Boil eggplant until tender, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain; reserve in separate containers the eggplant and 1 cup of the eggplant stock.
Saute 1 cup of the onions in butter until well browned.
Remove to separate bowl.
Cook corn in the same pan over medium heat for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the reserved cooked onions, reserved eggplant and the eggs, mixing well.
Add remaining 1/2 cup onions, bell peppers, garlic, salt, red and black peppers, 1 1/2 cups of cheese,
1 cup of the cracker crumbs and the reserved eggplant stock, mixing well.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top, then remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are lightly browned, cheese is melted and mixture bubbles around edges, about 40 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 side dish servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken).
Pour over chicken wings.
Best if marinated overnight.
Cook in a 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until dark golden brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients until well mixed.
Spread in layer pans and bake at 350°.
Ice with Strawberry Icing.

title: italian stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems and chop stems fine; set caps aside.
Combine chopped stems, cheese, parsley and Italian dressing in a bowl.
Stirring well, spoon mixture evenly into reserved mushroom caps and place in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 30 appetizers (about 8 calories each).

title: chicken pie
directions: Pull meat off the bone in little pieces.
Spread in oblong dish.
Mix chicken soup in chicken broth and pour over chicken. Combine flour, buttermilk and butter and pour over top.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini over low heat for 1 hour.
Mix sugar, pineapple and Sure-Jell.
Boil for 5 minutes and take off heat; add apricot jello and stir well, then add lemon juice.

title: lemon meringue pie(sugarless)
directions: Soften gelatin in dietetic beverage.
Add the juice of the lemon and the grated rind.
Add artificial sweetener (more if desired) and food coloring.
Set in refrigerator to harden.
After fully hardened, put in the blender and whip until fluffy.
Pour into 10-inch pie pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook butter, sugar and milk over low heat, stirring to soft ball stage (306°).
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until melted and mixed in.
Add the marshmallow cream and mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta process cheese spread and salsa in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl on High 5 minutes or until Velveeta cheese is melted, stirring after 3 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: tante anna's nut bread
directions: Place first four ingredients in sifter.
Mix egg, milk and nuts in bowl.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Mix well. Let stand in very well greased bread pan 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (sometimes longer).

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Top with onion slices.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over chops. Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes.

title: homemade lima beans(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Soak lima beans overnight and drain.
Cook for one hour.
Cool and refrigerate for one hour.
Place chopped onion, dry mustard, bacon drippings, molasses and brown sugar mixture in saucepan and simmer about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place with cooked limas and crumbled bacon in crock-pot and cook on low heat for about 6 1/2 hours.
Serves about 10 to 12.

title: taffy
directions: Boil ingredients until it forms a hard, crisp ball when dropped in cold water.
Don't stir!
Pour onto buttered plate until cool enough to pull.
Pull until white.
Twist into long string-like rope and break off in about 1-inch pieces.

title: easy hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in frypan. Add diced celery; mix with rest of ingredients. Pour in casserole. Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°. Yield: 6 servings.

title: orange cream cheese
directions: Remove orange zest and chop very fine.
Juice orange half and combine with sugar.
Put into a small saucepan.
Heat but do not boil.
Remove from heat. Add orange zest.
Allow mixture to cool. Add softened cream cheese. Blend thoroughly.

title: ozark raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in enough water to cover raisins.
Drain raisins and leave a small amount of water in them.
Mix sugar, sour cream and raisins.
Put in pie shell and put pie shell on top.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: orange drink
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender with 10 ice cubes. Serves 6.

title: spanish cornbread
directions: Add all ingredients except cheese, mix well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Add diced up Velveeta; pour in remaining batter.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: jerky
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch strips.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over meat.
Marinate overnight.
Remove from dish and dry with paper towels.
Put on rack and dry in slow 200° oven, about 2 1/2 hours or until very dry.

title: fabulous margarita
directions: Combine the water and tea bags in 1-cup glass measure. Microwave on full power 2 1/2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Remove tea bags. Stir in sugar and chill.

title: kenny's pizza dough
directions: Add yeast to 1/2 cup warm water and mix in large bowl.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Mix in the olive oil and salad oil.
Add the remaining 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Mix with hands.
May need to add more flour.
Mix until you are able to roll out for pizza.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain off grease.
Add cracker crumbs and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Peel and slice squash. Add squash.
Add mushrooms.
Place cheese on top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove lid for last few minutes.

title: sweetheart salad(from 1975 edition)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to pineapple.
Bring to boiling point, then stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add the lemon juice and cherry juice and let cool.

title: tomato soup to can
directions: Cook onions in a little water.
Wash celery and tomatoes and add to onions.
Cook until tender and put through a sieve.
Return the juice to the kettle and add sugar and salt.
Cream butter and flour or clear jell.
Bring to a boil and can.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Place all ingredients into a small crock-pot and cook on low, stirring occasionally.
This is good to make the night before so the flavors can blend.
Reheat on low the next day.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fruit punch
directions: Pour ginger ale and pineapple juice over sherbet.

title: white chocolate chex mix
directions: Gently mix all ingredients, except white chocolate. Spread in two 9 x 13-inch pans.

title: marinated barbecued chops
directions: In a bowl, combine soy sauce, honey and vinegar.
Blend in garlic powder and ginger.
Add oil and onion.
Place meat in plastic food bag. Pour marinade over the top. Close bag. Refrigerate 4 hours or longer, turning every hour.
Drain meat. Grill to desired taste, basting occasionally, with marinade. Serves 4.
(Can use roast also.)

title: earthquake cake
directions: In an oblong pan, spread chopped pecans.
On top of that place shredded coconut.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans.

title: beef spanish rice
directions: Saute onions, green pepper, rice (right from the box) and ground beef in the bacon drippings. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: macadamia nut cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla; beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture and beat for 2 minutes. Stir in nuts and chips. Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on cookie sheets for 1 minute before removing to wire racks.
Yield: about 6 dozen.

title: grandma graves cornbread dressing
directions: *You can boil and cut up fine extra giblets.

title: seafood cioppino
directions: In non-stick
skillet
heat
oil over medium-high heat. Add onion, green
pepper,
carrot and garlic.
Saute, stirring occasionally until soft,
about
5 minutes.
Transfer to large pot with
tight-fitting lid.
Add remaining ingredients except Swiss chard, fish,
clams,
prawns
and
parsley.
Simmer over medium-low heat 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients;
cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes, until prawns turn pink.
Serve with hot sourdough bread or rice.
Serves 4.

title: chopped liver
directions: Fry onions and liver in chicken fat.
Grind or process with eggs.
Season to taste.

title: mom's relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients together, using coarse blade on grinder.
Drain.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over ground vegetables.
Boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Put in hot jars; cover tightly with hot lids to seal.
Place on towel covered cupboard to seal and cool.

title: baked peach halves
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; sprinkle evenly over top of each peach half.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef enchilada
directions: Brown onions and beef in oil and set aside.
Heat 3 tablespoons of oil and flour, stirring until browned.
Slowly add chili powder mixture, stirring until thickened.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper and simmer about 5 minutes.
Soften tortillas by dipping in enough hot oil to cover and quickly remove from oil and drain.
Place some of meat mixture, cheese and diced onions on tortilla.
Place seam side down in baking dish.
Cover with remaining sauce and remaining meat, cheese and onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: louella's famous - donuts
directions: Mix together sugar and Crisco.
Pour scalding milk over mixture.
Stir dissolved yeast in very warm water, set aside.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Break up cake and put into large cake pan.
Mix the milk in pudding and ice cream.
Pour mixture over cake and refrigerate until set.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup of hot water.
Cut up strawberries and place in jello.
Pour strawberries and jello together over pudding.
Refrigerate until set.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkles.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: baked beans for a bunch(by pat boren)
directions: Fry
bacon and chop.
Fry hamburger and onions in bacon grease.
Mix
all
ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate velvet dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and walnuts; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.
Soften cream cheese; mix with powdered sugar and spread over crust.
Mix pudding as directed on package except use only 3 cups milk.
Add 1/2 of large carton Cool Whip with pudding; place mixture on top of crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
For best results, let set in refrigerator 1 day.

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar and Jell-O with hot water.
Add juices. Chill.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit.
Heat and pour over Jell-O.
Stir until Jell-O is dissolved and cool.
Add fruit and Coke.

title: low sugar o. j. cookies
directions: Mix and bake for 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put cooked rice in ungreased pan or casserole.
Place chicken breasts on top, or if preferred, cut up chicken may be mixed into rice.
Mix together 1 cup cream soup and 2 cups orange juice. Pour over the chicken and rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top. Cover and bake approximately 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Spread mustard on uncooked pie shell, then fill with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes (center should be set).
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: custard pudding
directions: Beat eggs separately.
Add to flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add milk, margarine and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat until pudding thickens, stirring frequently.
Place in bowl.
Serve hot or chill. Serves 8.

title: crisp 5-minute cabbage
directions: Heat milk and add the cabbage.
Simmer about 2 minutes.
Mix the flour and melted fat and add a little of the hot milk.
Stir the mixture into the cabbage and cook 3 or 4 minutes, or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: goulosh
directions: Mix all together and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: banana cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage into small pieces.
Do not shred as for cole slaw.
Add mayonnaise.
Chill about 45 minutes.
Add bananas no more than 15 minutes before serving to prevent them from browning.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Season and brown ground chuck.
Add tomato paste and let cool. When cool, add onion, green pepper and oregano.
Blend cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Cook noodles.
Place in casserole in layers, noodles, cheese and meat.
Repeat with meat on top.
Pour sherry over all (around edges).
Let stand overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to directions on box.
Cool; punch holes in cake with a fork.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut pina colada mix over cake.
(If desired, put strawberries on top of cake and then cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top.)
Refrigerate.
tags: cream of coconut pina colada mix

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Cut sides from bread; roll each slice flat with rolling pin. Combine cheese, chives and mayonnaise.
Spread cheese mixture on each slice.
Top with slice of ham.
Spread cheese mixture on top of ham.
Roll up, cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Can be done the night before.
At serving time, cut off ends.
Slice each roll in about 6 to 8 pieces.
Makes about 100 bite size pieces.

title: fruit drops
directions: Put in freezer for awhile, then dip in 6 ounces of chocolate chips and 1/2 block of paraffin, melted in double boiler.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: turmeric cake(sfoof)
directions: Mix the flour, semolina, turmeric and baking powder.
Dissolve the sugar in the milk; add them to the flour mixture along with the oil.
Beat well for 5 minutes.
Grease the pan or (baking tray) with the tahini generously and bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until cake is done.
Sprinkle the cake with pine nuts before the baking; then cut the cake in diamond shapes.
Serve with tea.

title: brine for smoked fish
directions: Soak fish for about 3 hours.
Take out and allow to dry. Smoke for 4 to 5 hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and slice chicken.
Cook broccoli as package directs. Arrange broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken. Sprinkle cheese over top, then bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can use more chicken and cheese, if desired.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble. Cook beef; add onion and saut until tender. Combine beef, onion, ketchup, salt, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar in Dutch oven or electric casserole. Add partially drained beans and stir gently to mix. Sprinkle with bacon. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pie(lite weight)
directions: Crumble crackers and add margarine and Equal.
Mix and press into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: taco chip dip
directions: Fry bacon and crumble. Brown turkey. Add taco seasoning (1 package to turkey, 2 packages to beans).
Grate cheeses.
Layer all in order given twice in crock-pot sprayed with nonstick spray. Heat through. Do not stir. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: light fruit cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put everything in a large bowl and mix with a tablespoon until mixed well.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Place rice, onion soup mix and mushrooms in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
To the top of this mixture, place pieces of chicken with salt and pepper to taste.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 45 minutes in
a 350° oven.

title: chinese pepper steaks
directions: Combine bouillon cube and water.
Mix cornstarch, soy sauce, salt and sugar together; marinate meat in it.
Set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in greased casserole dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: custard pie for company
directions: Scald milk. Stir beaten eggs into hot mixture slowly. Combine the remainder of ingredients except nutmeg. Pour custard into a deep pie shell. Grate or sprinkle nutmeg on top. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 275° until done.
Do not bake too fast. You do not want it to brown. Test with knife inserted in center for doneness. Bake about 40 minutes. Check often; ovens vary in degrees.

title: spicy pumpkin bars
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in pumpkin.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Gradually stir into creamed mixture.
Spread batter in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done. Cool in pan.
Spread with Cream Cheese Icing.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts or pecan halves.
Makes 32 bars.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple rice pudding
directions: Wash rice; drain. Boil in salted water until tender.
Drain; beat egg yolks. Add sugar, raisins, cinnamon and salt.
Pare and dice apples.
Add melted butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat egg whites stiff, not dry.
Fold into rice mixture.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake in moderate 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender. Serve hot.

title: salsa
directions: Mix lightly all ingredients. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet and sour roast
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into greased casserole.
Top with sauce.

title: coconut sugarless cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.

title: chicken fingers
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In shallow bowl, combine corn flakes, garlic powder and dry mustard.
Dip chicken pieces into melted butter; roll into crunch mixture, coating evenly.
Place on ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: miss fayes potato salad
directions: Drain potatoes and let cool. In a large mixing bowl mix mayonnaise, ketchup, mustard, pepper, and sweet pickles. Add a few potatoes and eggs at a time to the mayonnaise mixture, until both mixtures are combined.
Salt to taste, and enjoy.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine chicken with onion and pepper.
Layer alternately with tortillas in buttered shallow pan (11 x 15 x 2-inch).
Top with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with chili powder and garlic.
Add in order: chicken soup, mushroom soup and tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hot italian ham sandwiches
directions: Slice rolls in half.
Spread some paste on each side; sprinkle with oregano.
Add ham and cheese.
Wrap in foil and heat in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a plastic bag. Shake and mix. Set aside. Combine buttermilk
and baking powder in a bowl. Mix well. Dip 2 pieces of chicken in buttermilk mixture.
Place chicken in bag and shake to coat.
Place chicken in a shallow pan. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat 1-inch of oil in a large skillet to 325°. Add chicken and fry 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown, turning once.
Drain chicken on paper towels.

title: crock-pot squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion, carrots and soup.
Mix sour cream with flour.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Toss stuffing crumbs with butter and place half in crock-pot.
Add vegetable mixture.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Cook 7 to 9 hours on low.

title: baked fudgies
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sweepstakes salad(in honor of frank fox)
directions: Mix jello with boiling water; add pie filling and pineapple. Let jell.

title: souffled tomato omelet
directions: Place
sliced
tomatoes
in
iron
skillet with butter, salt, pepper
and drop of lemon juice. Cook down a few minutes until near serving consistency.
Stir in egg yolks and quickly fold in stiffly
beaten whites. Run under broiler until delicately brown. Serve immediately.

title: lasagna by janet
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix hamburger with sauce.
When noodles are done, rinse with cold water and drain.
Place some sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay 3 noodles over sauce.
Spread cottage cheese over noodles, then more sauce, 3 more noodles, Swiss cheese, sauce, noodles, Mozzarella cheese and rest of sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, onion, 1/2 tablespoon butter and pepper.
Turn into 1-quart casserole. Combine 1/4 cup crumbs and remaining butter.
Sprinkle over vegetable mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves about 6.

title: apple cider
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks and orange slices.
Serve. Yields 1 gallon.

title: sanctified ham balls
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat; blend in flour.
Add sour cream and seasonings.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Do not boil.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 2 cups boiling water. Add blueberry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan and blend until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils.
Boil and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and press plastic wrap onto surface.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.

title: asian slaw
directions: Remove flavor package from noodles, set aside.
Crush noodles by hand.
Place dry noodles in bottom of large bowl.
Top with slaw mix.
Sprinkle with nuts and onions.
Mix flavor packages from noodles, sugar, oil and vinegar, and pour mixture over slaw. Cover and chill 24 hours (need to let the noodles absorb dressing and get soft).
Toss well before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil, debone and cut up chicken.
Lay chicken in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix Veg-All, soup, cheese and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine. Add flour and milk.
Beat with wire whisk.
Pour slowly over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until light brown.

title: tea biscuits
directions: Combine sugar, flour and baking powder in a large bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender.
Add raisins.
In a separate bowl, combine milk, 1 egg and vanilla.
Blend with a whisk.
Quickly add liquids to dry and blend with wooden spoon.
Knead for 1 minute on floured board.
Roll out.
Cut into 3-inch squares. Place 2 squares together on top of each other on baking tray. Makes about 12 Tea Biscuits.
Brush biscuits with beaten egg, then bake for about 15 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Grease two (9-inch) round layer cake pans.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs for cake-like brownies.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
In a large bowl mix sweetened condensed milk and water.
Beat in pudding mix.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place one brownie layer on serving plate.
Top with half each of the pudding mixture and strawberries.
Add second layer and remainder of pudding mixture and strawberries. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cornmeal dumplings
directions: Mix meal, flour, baking powder and eggs.
Add milk, stirring until well blended.
Add melted bacon fat.
Drop by teaspoons into boiling broth.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour and salt.
Add oats.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar and milk icing while hot.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add syrup, eggs, salt and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake 5 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 350° until firm.

title: cardinal salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Chill until slightly thickened. Add apples, celery, salt and lemon juice.
Pour into 2-quart ring and mold.
Chill until firm.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let cookie dough soften and spread onto a large pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake, according to directions on the cookie package, 10 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned. Let cool.

title: korean beef patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into four balls and flatten into patties.
Broil, grill or panfry until done.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven or large frypan.
Stir in flour gradually; add half and half and stir until thickened.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Cook and stir until smooth.
Fold in seafood. Heat 3 minutes; stir occasionally.
Toss pasta with sauce or spoon on top.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: mom's pancakes
directions: Add all ingredients, stirring thoroughly, and adding more or less milk as needed.
Fry on a hot greased griddle.
Serve with Brown Sugar Syrup.

title: chicken with white wine
directions: Coat chicken breasts with a mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Shake off and reserve excess flour.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Brown chicken on both sides; remove.
Add remaining oil, mushrooms and onion.
Saute until onion is tender.
Stir in reserved flour; mix in wine.
Return to skillet with parsley. Simmer 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: old-time southern corn muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and milk.
Add flour sifted with salt and baking powder.
Add corn meal, stirring only enough to mix.
Fill greased muffin pans two-thirds full; bake in hot oven (425°) for 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.
May use nonstick cooking spray (Pam) to grease muffin tin, if preferred.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a double boiler, stirring until it thickens.
Cover and cook 10 more minutes, stirring occasionally. Add egg yolks, margarine and vanilla; stir well.
Pour into an already baked pie crust in 8 or 9-inch pan.

title: enchilada bake
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Add seasonings; drain.
Add soups, milk, green chilies and sauce.
Cook over low heat.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with crushed chips.
Pour half of mixture over chips.
Top with chips and half of cheese.
Pour remaining mixture.
Top with chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Puree ingredients in blender.
Great on broiled chicken or fish.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows. Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies.
Press in sides and bottom of a 10-inch pie tin. Fill with ice cream and pour strawberries on top.
Put in freezer and freeze.
About 10 minutes before you serve dessert, remove from the freezer.
Return unused portion to freezer.

title: crab meat puff
directions: Combine all ingredients (except muffins) and spread mixture onto muffin halves.
Cut each muffin into 6 triangles.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or wrap well and freeze for later use.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: sweet sour chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and roll in cornstarch, then in beaten eggs.
Brown chicken in frypan until golden brown.
Place in baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients to make sauce and pour over chicken pieces.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add eggs, water and pumpkin. Mix well. Sift dry ingredients. Add to pumpkin mixture, just enough to mix well. Add dates, raisins and nuts.
Bake in floured and greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour. Test with a toothpick in center of loaf.
If it comes out clean with no dough clinging to it, the bread is done.
Otherwise bake until done.
Check often.

title: nomie's best lemon pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add boiling water, then milk.
Mix and cook until thick and smooth.
Beat egg yolks; gradually add with butter, juice and rind to cooked mixture.
Continue to cook slowly until thick and mixture drops from spoon in sheets.

title: jello popsicles
directions: Mix well and pour into popsicle maker.

title: golden fish fillets
directions: Lightly beat together egg, mustard and salt in a shallow dish. Put potato flakes in another shallow dish.
Dip fish fillets in egg mixture, then roll in potato flakes to coat.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Fry fish for 3 to 4 minutes on each side, until it is golden brown and flakes easily with a fork.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Blend juice and sugar together.
Add the cream and food coloring.
Pour into freezer tray and quick freeze for at least 3 hours.
Do not stir.
May use other flavors or even add fruits to this.
Nuts or marshmallows can also be added for special changes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Chop apples into bite size pieces to fill a glass pie pan. Sprinkle cut apples with cinnamon.
Melt butter in pan over low heat.
Add peanut butter and sugar.
Heat until melted.
Add oats and stir until all oats are coated.
Spread evenly over apples to form a crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until apples are soft.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir carrots and onion in shortening until onion is tender.
Add water to pineapple syrup to make 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Stir in cornstarch and soy sauce.
Add to vegetables and pop in the 2 bouillon cubes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Let boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add chicken and pineapple.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Any other cubed meat may be substituted.
Pork is great!

title: banana and peanut butter shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Whirl until smooth. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: shortcut cookies
directions: Empty cake mix into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until blended.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheets. Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen. Store in airtight container.

title: easy rice almond pilaf
directions: In a skillet or 2-quart saucepan with lid, combine margarine and almonds.
Saute on high heat until slightly brown.
Add water, rice, onion soup mix, parsley, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cover tightly with lid, making sure no steam is escaping from the top.
Reduce heat to simmer and continue cooking for 20 minutes or until all water is absorbed. Leave covered while cooking.

title: alice dick's butterscotch pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Blend in 1/2 cup milk.
Add 5 cups very warm milk; bring to boil.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add 1 cup mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Boil 1 minute.
Add oleo or butter and vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Pour into 2 large pie shells or three 8-inch shells. Cover with meringue.
Bake for 12 minutes at 475°.

title: hodgie podgies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on buns.
(The 4 buns make 8 halves.)
Put under broiler until done.

title: savory baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake covered in greased casserole in moderate 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: holiday fudge
directions: Combine powdered sugar, milk, butter and salt in a 5-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until chocolate has melted and begins to thicken.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased 17 x 11-inch pan.
Let cool.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Place chocolate, Eagle Brand milk and butter in pan; cook about 4 minutes, stirring all the time.
Have dry unsalted peanuts and marshmallows in large bowl.
Pour chocolate over and stir until mixed.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan greased with butter. Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: frozen butterfinger pie
directions: Soften yogurt or ice cream for 20 minutes on counter.
Spoon half of yogurt/ice cream into crust.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Remove seeds from pumpkin.
Separate seeds from strings.
Soak in salt water for one hour.
Drain.
Spread pumpkin seeds in jelly roll pan.
Salt lightly.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: caramel candy
directions: Mix brown and white sugars and Milnot until moistened.
Add vinegar and cook until soft ball in water test.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat with mixer until thickened.
Put in greased 9 x 3 x 11-inch pan.
Cool.
Yields 2 1/2 to 3 pounds.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into a greased and lightly floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours to 2 hours.
Careful, doesn't always take this long.

title: corona's company chicken
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put chicken pieces on top of 1 cup of rice and cover with sauce.
Cover with one package of Lipton onion soup mix.

title: six week muffins
directions: Add sugar to warm, melted shortening.
Beat in eggs.
Mix cereal, flour and salt together and add to first mixture.
Measure baking soda into buttermilk and add to mixture.
Grease and flour (or line) muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cover and store up to 6 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: kubie (syrian meat loaf)
directions: Soak 1 cup cracked wheat in 3 cups hot water and set aside. Mix onion, salt, pepper and spices with ground beef.
Drain excess water off cracked wheat.
Add cracked wheat to meat mixture and mix well.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Press mixture into pan. Dip a sharp knife into cool water and cut into diamond shape pieces.
In three different places, make holes with a spoon and pour a little oil in each hole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can use 1/2 lamb and 1/2 beef or you could use all lamb, if you'd like.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix into dough.
Chill.
Roll and cut with cookie cutter.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
Pour cooked rice into large casserole dish.
Cook ground beef; drain off grease and add to rice.
Pour in can of tomato sauce; mix well.
Add corn and mix well.
Add onions and oregano; mix well.
Finally, add pepper and stewed tomatoes; mix in well.
Place lid on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325° or in microwave 15 minutes on High.

title: brussels sprouts casserole
directions: Bring all of the ingredients to a boil.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes together.
Drain vegetables.
Pour sauce over and toss lightly.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: In large bowl, toss together black-eyed peas, tomatoes, zucchini, green beans, corn and onion.
In a shaker jar, measure vinegar, oil, cilantro, sugar and cumin.
Cover and shake well. Pour over salad and toss to combine.
Cover and chill 2 to 24 hours.

title: moravian chicken pie
directions: Make crust for double crust pie with 2 cups flour.
Cut in shortening.
Add salt and ice water to make a pastry that clings together.
Divide into halves.
Roll out one half on lightly floured board.
Line a 9-inch pie pan.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl. Make holes in ingredients; add oil, vanilla and vinegar to each hole. Pour water over all. Beat well; pour into cake pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion until done in a large pot.
Turn heat down very low so it will no longer boil.
Just simmer.
Add margarine.
In shaker or with whisk, combine milk and flour and add to soup mixture to thicken.
Add grated Velveeta cheese; simmer until melted.

title: california guacamole
directions: Cut avocados and mix well with lemon juice and onion.
Add 2 tablespoons Pace picante sauce and mix well.

title: easy cream cheese pastry
directions: Grease a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Press one package of rolls onto pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and lemon juice. Cover the flattened rolls with cream cheese mixture. Press out second package of rolls
onto waxed paper. Transfer this thin layer of crescent rolls onto cream cheese layer. Remove waxed paper.
Paint with egg white.
Sprinkle with sugar and slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool and serve.

title: syrian bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to flour and salt.
Mix real good.
(You may need to add more water.)
Cover with cloth, plastic and blanket.
Let raise real high and cut it into 1 1/2 pound balls.
Lay on cloth and cover for 30 minutes or more.
Then pound down.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Put into pans.
Stretch into round pans.
Prick top of bread with fork and glaze with milk. Put in oven until bottom is brown.
Then take off pan and put on top rack.

title: steve pond's chicken chicka-dillo
directions: Saute chicken in olive oil.
Add and saute for 3 minutes the garlic, cumin and oregano.
Remove and reserve chicken.
Add the butter to hot pan and saute peppers and onion which you've chopped.
Add tomatoes (with juice) and cook on low heat for 1/2 hour.
Now, add remaining ingredients and chicken.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Stir a few times.

title: tea party pecan balls
directions: Combine
oleo,
sugar,
wafer
crumbs and thawed orange juice. Mix
well.
Roll into small balls, then into pecans or coconut. Refrigerate until served.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line a well-greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with graham crackers, fitted tightly together, with no cracks between.
If necessary, break crackers to fit.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar and margarine.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes, no longer, just to melt sugar.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes, no longer. Confection should be bubbly.
Partly cool, then cut in bars.
Lift from pan and cool completely on rack.
(If you waited too long and cookies are stuck to pan, return to oven just long enough to loosen.)
When bars are completely cool, can be stored in tightly covered container or frozen up to a month.

title: chilled mexican appetizer
directions: First Layer:
bean dip, tomato paste and green chilies.

title: hot peppers
directions: Mix together and boil 5 minutes.
Put peppers (removing seed veins with rubber gloves on) in hot jars.
Pour hot mixture over them and seal; let sit overnight before moving.

title: finger sandwiches
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with chopped watercress, olives or chives.
Spread between thin slices of bread with crust trimmed. Cut into thirds.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt oleo; stir in sugar and milk.
Cook 5 minutes on High. Add chocolate bits, vanilla and nuts.
Stir only until melted. Pour in buttered 5 x 11-inch or 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: eggplant pattie
directions: Peel and dice eggplant and cook in a little water until very tender.
Drain well in a strainer, add other ingredients and mix well.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in hot skillet and drop by spoonfuls. Brown one side, turn to brown other side.

title: firenze salad
directions: Combine beans, squash, garlic and dressing in a non-metal bowl; stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours to blend.
Add tomato and cheese just before serving.
Toss lightly.

title: squash souffle
directions: Boil and mash enough squash to make 2 cups (drained).
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Melt butter and add to squash. Crumble and add whole wheat bread to squash.
Stir well and turn into greased casserole.
Sprinkle grated sharp cheese on top and bake uncovered about 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: potato cheese puff
directions: Bring water, margarine and salt to boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in milk and potatoes.
Cool slightly.
Beat in eggs, Cheddar cheese and pepper until well blended.
Turn into well-greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated 400° oven 25 to 30 minutes until golden, puffed and set. Serve at once.

title: microwave stir-fried spinach
directions: Heat butter
4 minutes on High.
This will brown and be very hot.
Preheat
large
microwave
browning
skillet 4 1/2 minutes on High.
Add browned butter, spinach and onion.
Stir quickly, cover
and cook on High 2 minutes or until done.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Mix in onion.
Beat egg with milk; stir in.
Drop by small spoonfuls into deep, hot fat.
Puppies will float when done.
Drain on paper towels.

title: spinach dressing
directions: Place in a blender and spin until smooth.
Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in an 8 or 9-inch square pan, starting with potatoes.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over layers.
Bake at 400° for 55 minutes.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Combine with remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight. (Rolls should not be expected to rise very much.) Knead and roll out dough. Cover and let rise 1 hour. cut dough in triangles and roll into crescent shapes. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. (Rolls freeze nicely.)

title: french toast
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.	Mix egg and milk.
Add to flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Dip bread in mixture and fry until toasty brown.
(Wheat bread is very good.)

title: chocolate cake
directions: Place dry ingredients in bowl.
Mix completely.
Make a well and pour in vanilla, vinegar and oil.
Pour cold water over top. Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour before cutting, then set out 1 hour before baking.
Bake at 400° until done, about 30 minutes cooking time.

title: hawaiian ham spread
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese and pineapple together until smooth.
Stir in ham and coconut.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with crackers of your choice. Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put cinnamon and sugar in small bowl.
Roll the quartered biscuit pieces in this mixture.
Put into a greased Bundt or tube pan.
Boil brown sugar, butter and water for 2 minutes and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.
Let stand for a few minutes before inverting on serving platter. Pinch off to eat and enjoy.

title: zesty italian pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish. Cover pork chops and bottom of baking dish with Italian dressing. Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste. To spice it up a little, shake a few drops of Texas Pete or some other hot sauce on each pork chop.

title: quick lasagna
directions: In an 11 x 14-inch dish, spread out 3 or 4 tablespoons of Prego.
Cook egg noodles, drain and spread out evenly in dish. Spread out cottage cheese or sour cream, sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese.
Brown and drain hamburger and mix with remaining Prego. Spread evenly over top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until evenly heated and bubbly.

title: cinnamon apple milkshake
directions: Place ice cream and milk in a blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Makes 2 (8 ounce) servings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix the ground beef and soup in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over the mix and top it off with the Tater Tots.
Cook at 300° until the Tater Tots are brown and the cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 layer pans, 8 or 9-inches, or oblong pan (13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inches).
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar; continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Set meringue aside.
Measure flour and blend with baking powder, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Mix together oil, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Add this and half the milk to flour mixture.
Beat 1 minute.
Scrape bottom and sides of bowl often. Add remaining milk and egg yolks.
Beat 1 minute.
Fold in meringue.
Bake layers 30 to 35 minutes, oblong 40 to 45 minutes. Cool and ice cake.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix all salad ingredients together.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together in 1 1/2-quart Pyrex bowl.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour over the boiling water; stir in to combine.
Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
When batter is cooled to lukewarm, add yeast.
Stir in 1 cup whole wheat flour and 4 cups white flour.
When dough is stiff enough to handle, turn onto floured board; knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; cover and let rise until doubled.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, salt, flour and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture begins to thicken, carefully and quickly stir in well-beaten egg yolks.
Stir until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pie shell.

title: yellow squash muffins
directions: Wash squash thoroughly; trim off ends (or peel the squash if it is large).
Cut squash in 1-inch slices.
Cook in small amount of water until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Measure enough of squash to equal 2 cups.
Combine squash, eggs and butter; stir well and set aside.
Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in the center of mixture.
Add squash mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.
Spoon into well-greased muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: cranberry-orange glaze
directions: Brush on during last 20 minutes of cooking.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix.
Put in 9 x 13 pan.
On top of mixture mix 1/2 cup crumbs and 1/2 cup oleo.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cream cheese pineapple pie
directions: Combine 1/3 cup sugar, cornstarch and pineapple plus juice in a small saucepan. Cook over medium heat until mixture is thick and clear.

Cook and set aside. Blend softened cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in mixer bowl. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Blend in milk and vanilla. Spread cooled pineapple mixture on bottom of pie shell.
Pour cheese mixture over pineapple layer and sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Continue baking at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly. Stir in orange peel and juice.
Stir dry ingredients together; blend into shortening mixture.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until cookies are delicately browned on edges or until almost no imprint remains when lightly touched with finger.
Frost with Orange Butter Icing.
Makes 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Put in crock-pot at bedtime on low to be ready to eat at noon or put in crock-pot in the morning on low to be ready for night meal.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400 degrees.
(Do Not Overbake.)

title: lite fruit bowl
directions: Mix all the fruit together.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over fruit.
Stir until pudding is moist.
Chill overnight.

title: mama's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding cheese last.
Bake in greased iron skillet at 400° for 45 minutes.
(May use another bread pan if desired, greased and floured.)
Serves 8 to 12.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Coat biscuit pieces with this mixture.
Place in ungreased angel food pan.
Mix margarine and 1/2 cup of sugar; bring to a boil.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Set 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: creamed sherry chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl, except chicken. If mixture seems thick, add a little more dry sherry.
Lay chicken breasts in a Pyrex pan.
Pour mixture over chicken covering as completely as possible.
Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Best served with noodles or rice. Serves 4.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam before placing chicken breasts inside (all right if meat is still frozen some). Put cheese on top of chicken. Mix soup, wine, mushrooms and 1/2 of oleo together. Spoon on each breast. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. I bake mine 70.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Work shortening into flour.
Add sugar.
Dissolve yeast in water, then add along with milk to flour.
Knead dough; make into biscuits.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: giant cookie
directions: Mix until moistened.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: creamed corn corn bread
directions: Make each corn bread mix according to directions on box. After you have made the corn bread mixture, add the can of creamed corn.
Stir well.
Pour on hot griddle, sprayed with Pam, and cook like pancakes.
Serve hot with butter.
Goes real well with beans and ham!

title: stuffed artichokes*
directions: Wash artichokes thoroughly and trim points with scissors. Separate the leaves and stuff each leaf well with mixture.
Cook in deep well or steam cooker for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: moist apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat oil and sugar together thoroughly. Add eggs and beat until mixture is creamy.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Stir into batter.
Ad all the remaining ingredients and stir to blend.
Turn mixture into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan before turning out.
Serve at room temperature with ice cream, if desired.

title: german (apple) pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, milk, vanilla and sugar.
Sift in flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in fresh fruit(s).
Melt butter in 10-inch skillet (with handle removed).
Pour in batter; top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 15 to 25 minutes at 350° to 375°, until top is golden and toothpick comes out clean.
Serve in wedges with your favorite sauce.

title: fried squash and onions
directions: Wash and cut onion in small cubes.
Put in skillet with about 3 tablespoons shortening and 1 cup water.
Cover with lid and cook slowly until tender.
Remove lid and let liquid fry down low.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: never fail noodles
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add sifted flour.
Mix and make into a dough.
Roll out onto a floured board; let dry.
Roll up and cut into desired size noodles.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix in blender and pour into fluted Bundt pan.
Freeze.
(It is pretty to decorate top with mint leaves and strawberries.)
This makes 2 Bundt pans frozen.
Pour into punch bowl and let soften, then pour over 7-Up.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as package directs.
Add seasonings and onion to taste.
Slice chicken breasts along side to form a pocket.
Salt inside of pocket.
Fill pockets with stuffing. Place a small pat of butter inside.

title: pizzelles
directions: Make like cookie dough.
Add 1 teaspoon baking powder.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, oil and flavoring.
Add flour and remaining baking powder.
Drop from teaspoon to pizzelle iron.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
May add to flavor one of the following:
1 tablespoon rum, 2 tablespoons cocoa or 2 tablespoons cinnamon.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and onion.
Set aside.
Mix bouillon cube with water and cream of mushroom soup; set aside.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, both sugars and peanut butter.
Add eggs to mixture.
Add soda to boiling water; mix well and pour into cream mixture.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Form balls on greased sheet and press with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: modified twice baked potatoes
directions: Note:
Eliminate or use scant sprinkling of low sodium salt.

title: chili and beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Combine the remaining ingredients and add to the ground beef.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes on medium heat.
Continue to simmer, uncovered, until mixture has thickened.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix and pour into 2 pie crusts and bake at 325°.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix and pour into ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cut up salt pork, render fat in pan with 2 tablespoons oil. Remove pork rind from pan and add onions and celery, barely cover with water.
Cut potatoes bite size and add to onion and celery when almost done.
Add clams, margarine and cream; simmer.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Sift flour once, measure and sift with soda and salt.

Cream together shortening, sugars, vanilla, water and eggs at high speed with electric mixer, scraping bowl frequently with rubber spatula. Remove beaters and with heavy spoon, stir in flour mixture, then oatmeal, then chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 1/2-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes or until just set.
Remove from baking sheet immediately and cool on wax paper.
Store in tightly covered container. Yield: 12 1/2 dozen.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water to frothy stage.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Dip pecans in egg white, then roll in sugar mixture. Place in shallow pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Great for the holidays.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients and turn into buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for one hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: chunky pimento cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients, stir well.
Cover and chill.
Yield: 2 1/4 cups.

title: holiday salad
directions: Drain pineapple, oranges and cherries.
Mix jello according to directions. Add pineapple to lime jello. Add cherries and oranges to cherry jello.
Pour lime mixture into a trifle bowl. Refrigerate until well set.
Pour in cherry mixture.
Refrigerate until well set. Top with Cool Whip, then sprinkle with chopped nuts or coconut, if desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: connie's broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in a saucepan until done.
Melt butter; crumble up Ritz crackers in melted butter.
Put in bottom of baking dish. Pour broccoli over Ritz crackers.
Slice cheese on top of broccoli.
Place in 400° oven for about 15 minutes until cheese melts.

title: lemon cake cookies
directions: Roll in balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place cut up chicken in shallow baking dish.
Melt margarine in small saucepan. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, basting often.

title: savory shepherds pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cook onion and green peppers until tender (use shortening if needed).
Drain hamburger.
Stir in soup, onion, green peppers, salt and thyme.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spoon mashed potatoes around edge of casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: strawberry jam
directions: You will need 4 (8-ounce) freezing containers.

title: chex and nut nibbles
directions: In a saucepan, melt the butter and chocolate chips together, stirring until smooth.
In a large bowl, combine the dry cereal and mixed nuts.
Pour chocolate mixture over the mixture in the bowl.
With rubber spatula, carefully mix until cereal and nuts are thoroughly covered.
Sprinkle 1 cup of the powdered sugar and the cinnamon and nutmeg over the top.
Mix until blended.
Add remaining powdered sugar, 1 cup at a time, blending until the pieces are all coated with the sugar.
Store in covered containers in a cool place.
Serve as nibbles.

title: juanita's mixed bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: fresh green bean salad
directions: Bring water and 1/2 teaspoon salt to a boil in large pan. Drop in beans and boil briskly, uncovered, for 10 minutes or less. Beans should be tender, but still slightly resistant to the bite. Drain beans and transfer to serving bowl.
Blend vinegar, remaining salt, mustard and pepper together with whisk in small bowl.
Continue beating with whisk and add oil slowly.
Whisk until smooth.
Pour dressing over beans in serving bowl.
Add tomatoes and onions; toss with wooden spoons.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: In bowl, make a batter of the warm mashed sweet potatoes by adding well-beaten egg yolks, salt, sugar, butter and enough cream or milk to give mixture the consistency of cake batter.
In bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold them into batter.
Pour into a buttered baking dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake in 350° oven until marshmallows are melted and nicely browned.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add pepper.
Turn into skillet; cook until firm.
In pan, cut into strips 1/2-inch wide.
Add onion, meat, soy sauce, sugar and pepper; blend well. Cook, stirring gently, until hot.
Serve.

title: kolachky
directions: In a standing mixer fitted with a paddle, or in a bowl using a hand held beater, cream the butter, cream cheese and sugar until well blended.
Add the egg and mix until incorporated.
Add the flour and mix until incorporated.
Wrap the dough in plastic wrap and chill overnight.

title: marguerite's jelly roll(laisy-daisy cake)
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, flour, and baking powder, salt together. Bring to boil milk and butter, mix together and add vanilla.
Bake in a greased jelly roll pan or cookie sheet for about 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Put powdered sugar on wax paper, dump cake on wax paper while warm.
Spread with jelly then roll up.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs, molasses, flour, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and soda mixture.
Batter will be thin. Pour in a greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake 45 minutes in 300° oven.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Grind cranberries.
Grate 1 orange rind and add to other ingredients.
Drain one 15 ounce can crushed pineapple and add to sauce.
Save juice.

title: sunset strip barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in bacon fat until brown.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.

title: shrimp etouffee(servings:  12)
directions: Saute onions in bacon grease.
Add Worcestershire sauce, black and red pepper, Tabasco sauce, garlic salt and salt.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Add mushroom soup, celery soup and water. Add bacon and white wine.
Garnish with chopped green onions and tops.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: mexican macaroni dinner
directions: In large skillet, heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes, breaking into pieces with spoon.
Add beans and corn. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Toss in macaroni and heat for 5 more minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and serve.

title: banana cake
directions: Mash and cream bananas with a fork. Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake 375° for 35 - 40 minutes.

title: gallagher's beer-cheese soup
directions: *Or use 2 ounces imitation bacon bits.

title: southwestern beef and beans(8 servings)
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Brown salt pork in skillet; drain off fat in paper towel.
In slow cooking pot, combine soaked beans with water, browned pork and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook for 1 hour on high, then on low for 8 to 9 hours.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: In medium saucepan combine chocolate chips and butter.
Cook on very low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Add milk.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla; blend well.
Shape 1 tablespoon of dough around each candy kiss.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Melt baking bar and oil over low heat while stirring. Drizzle over cookies.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place green beans in dish, then the corn on top. Mix other ingredients and pour on top of corn.

title: kool-aid sherbet
directions: Place can of cream in freezer; chill 1 hour.
Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid in water.
Place chilled cream in cold mixing bowl and whip until thick.
Add Kool-Aid; blend well.
Pour in large pan and freeze.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into cake pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
May also sprinkle cheese on top and bake also.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Cook in broth until tender. In another pot, melt butter slowly.
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Whisk in half and half slowly.
(If lumps develop, I blend in food processor.)
Add butter, flour and half and half mixture to broccoli/broth mixture.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease an oblong 2-quart baking dish. Mix first 9 ingredients and spread evenly in dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and crushed potato chips.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Thaw spinach.
Butter a large baking pan.
Process bread into fine crumbs.
Chop onion.
Cook onion in oil until soft, about 2 minutes.
Whisk eggs with milk, basil, salt and pepper.
Add spinach, onion, turkey, bread crumbs and lemon juice.
Mix well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream up first four ingredients.
Mix well beaten eggs and other ingredients.
Make 1-inch balls and flatten; place 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 minutes at 325°.

title: broccoli spears with lime butter
directions: Cook broccoli.
Drain.
Place in serving dish.
Melt butter in small saucepan; stir in lime juice.
Pour over broccoli spears, season with salt and pepper.

title: monkey bread
