directions: Dissolve the yeast and 1 teaspoon of sugar in warm water. Combine 1/2 cup butter, 1/3 cup sugar, salt and milk.
Heat until lukewarm.
Beat the eggs in large bowl.
Add yeast and milk mixtures and 1/2 of the flour; mix well.
Add the rest of the flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and satiny, 5 to 8 minutes.

title: favorite brownies
directions: Nuts and chocolate chips can be used instead of M&M's.

title: large pearl tapioca pudding(dear mary smallwood's recipe)
directions: Soak tapioca overnight or 24 hours in 2 cups water.
The next, day, empty liquid and all in a heavy pan.
Add flour and stir. Add egg yolks, sugar and milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick and tapioca is transparent.
Beat egg whites with 2 tablespoons very cold water until stiff, then fold into tapioca mixture and add vanilla.

title: ham delights
directions: Cut ham, onion and cheese in food processor bowls with steel blade.
Process until finely chopped.
Add mustard, poppy seed, margarine and Worcestershire sauce to ham mixture.
Mix by hand. Take rolls out of package by the whole thing.
Slice off tops of rolls halfway down.
Spread with mixture and replace top.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 48 small sandwiches.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Add chicken or seasoning meat to season.
Cook 1 hour.

title: oatmeal fudge bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in baking mix and oats until uniform consistency.
Heat chocolate chips, milk, 2 tablespoon margarine and salt in 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Press about 2/3 of oatmeal mixture in pan.* Spread chocolate mixture over oatmeal layer.
Drop remaining oatmeal mixture by tablespoons onto top.
Bake until light brown, about 30 minutes.
Cool completely. Cut into bars about 2 x 1-inch.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion. Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with shredded cheese if desired.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs and beat well. Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well. Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Grease loaf pan; line pan with waxed paper and cake is easily removed.

title: barbecued beef or pork
directions: In a Dutch oven, place meat, onion and celery; cover with water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender. Remove meat.
Strain and save the liquid. Trim the meat of fat and shred the meat.
Return to the pot and add 2 cups liquid.
Mix all seasonings and add to meat mixture. Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
If too thick, add additional liquid.
Serve on hamburger rolls. Freezes well. Save some liquid for thinning.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Heat salted water to boiling. Add broccoli. Cover and heat to boiling. Cook until stems are tender, 12 to 15 minutes.
Drain. Arrange broccoli in ungreased baking dish. Heat oven to 400°. Beat soup and milk with hand mixer until smooth.
Pour over broccoli.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly. Sprinkle over cheese sauce. Bake until crumbs are very light brown (about 20 minutes).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Mix cornflour with a little milk.
Stir it into lukewarm milk in a saucepan, with yolk of egg, and bring to the boil, stirring all the time.
Boil for 2 minutes, then remove from heat and cool for a few minutes.
Then stir in grated cheese and stiffly beaten white of egg.
Pour into a greased baking dish and cook for about 20 minutes in a hot oven.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix the first five ingredients and add flour to make a stiff dough.
Grease a large bowl with oil, put in the dough and turn over so the oily side is on top.
Cover and let stand overnight. Do not refrigerate.
Next morning, punch down the dough and knead lightly.
Divide into 3 equal parts.
Knead each portion 8 times. Put into greased loaf pans and let rise 4 to 6 hours.
Cover with wax paper while rising.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Brush with butter and turn out to cool.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients together, adding eggs one at a time. Stir in walnuts.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes; cool.

title: "best ever" cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients. Roll in balls the size of a walnut and flatten slightly or drop by teaspoon and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, depending on your oven and desired doneness.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef (drain).
Mix first 5 ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
No lid.

title: orange cookies
directions: Add baking soda to sour milk.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and orange juice (or rind, if used).
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with sour milk and baking soda mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add red and yellow food coloring to make desired shade of orange (this is optional).

title: oriental fried chicken
directions: Bone chicken and cut into large chunks.
Combine salt, soy sauce, rice wine, ginger and garlic.
Add chicken to soy sauce mixture and marinate 2 hours, stirring occasionally, to coat all the chicken pieces.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Roll chicken in cornstarch and deep fry at 375° until brown and crispy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: roadside potatoes
directions: Heat half and half, margarine and salt until margarine melts. Spread hash browns in 9 x 13 pan.
Pour heated mixture over potatoes.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour, uncovered.

title: tea balls(dessert)
directions: Mix together and roll into small balls.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Roll in 10x sugar while still warm.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper together.
Pour off grease and rinse, if desired.
Put in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Add mushrooms, soup and cheese.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake covered for 30 minutes at 400°, then 10 minutes uncovered.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Whip egg whites on medium speed until soft peaks form. Continue whipping on medium speed while gradually adding sugar and baking powder.
Continue to whip until very stiff peaks form and all sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Coarsely break saltines and with 3/4 cup pecans fold by hand into mixture. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 300° for 30 minutes until center is almost firm.
Do not overbake!!!
Remove from oven and cool upside down.
When thoroughly cooled, top with whip topping and sprinkle with 1/4 cup pecans.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add egg yolks.
Blend in 2 cups flour.
Coat fruit and nuts with remaining 2 cups flour.
Fold in all other ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: beth's tea muffins
directions: Mix together.
Spoon into small muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hot spiced fruit
directions: Mix together all ingredients with the fruits undrained. Simmer for 1 hour.
Try fixing in a crock-pot.
This is good with sliced ham or even over ice cream.

title: tiny meatballs
directions: Mix together and shape into small balls and put in shallow pan.
Dredge with 1/4 cup vegetable oil.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
While bake prepare sauce.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In it, combine sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves and mixture reaches boiling point.
Cook without stirring to hard ball stage (250°).
Remove from heat.

title: hobo beans
directions: Fry bacon; crumble.
Brown hamburger with onion and bacon. Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sugar and cream cheese, beating until well blended.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Refrigerate.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: tang salad
directions: Mix dry ingredients and juice together and pour over fruit.

title: warm shrimp and potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a medium-size saucepan and cover with water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 12 minutes or until tender.
Add shrimp, cook 2 minutes or until done.
Drain and rinse with cold water; drain.
In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, milk, capers, vinegar, salt, mustard and pepper, stirring with a whisk.
Add potatoes, shrimp and onion; toss to coat.
Serve over greens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: key lime cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9x13 pan or bundt pan.	Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Let cake cool in pan.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Toast sesame seeds in a small frying pan over medium heat, shaking frequently until golden brown (approximately 5 minutes). Transfer seeds to a small bowl, blend with honey, mustard, sherry and lemon juice.
Arrange chicken breasts slightly apart in a pan. Pour sesame seed mixture evenly over chicken.
Bake uncovered in oven at 400°.
Baste several times with sesame mixture until meat is done.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Mash out lumps of meat; add salt.
Add chili seasoning and stir until all is mixed in.
Let all cook together for about 3 minutes.
Add beans and soup and mix well. Add 1/2 to 1 can of water and stir well.
Reduce heat to low. Allow to simmer 45 minutes to
hour, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: flank steak
directions: Marinate steak in mixture of oil, wine vinegar, garlic, parsley and black pepper for 2 hours at room temperature.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Cook sugar and rhubarb on low heat for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add strawberry jello.
Stir well.
Put into jars and seal.

title: norwegian pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together potatoes, sugar, milk, margarine, eggs and vanilla, and pour into 1 1/2 to 2 quart casserole.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Save egg whites and strawberry juice for frosting.

title: vidalia dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 1-quart casserole. Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Serve hot. Simple and delicious.

title: governor's choice marinated steak
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour over steak and marinate all day. Broil steak 6 minutes on one side and 5 minutes on the other side or put on grill. Cut in strips.
Serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: a salad for company
directions: Serve on chilled plates and pour Honey Dijon dressing on lightly and serve.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water to a boil; add oil and salt.
Stir in flour all at once; beat over low heat until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat until the mixture is shiny.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Cool.
Fill with cream filling.

title: dirt cups("kids love these")
directions: Will also need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) clear plastic cups.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and milk. Add coconut and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned raisin bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, beaten eggs, cooled milk, butter and vanilla.
Place bread crumbs in casserole and dust with cinnamon and pour mixture over all.
Set casserole in pan of hot water; bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes, until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve warm with butterscotch sauce.

title: chicken with apricot preserves
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and onion soup mix together and heat. Pour over chicken in a flat baking dish and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice).
Mix pineapple with marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix juice from pineapple with flour, sugar, vinegar and egg.
Cook until thick.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl and beat until well blended.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie crust and bake at 350°
for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Combine and pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Mix well and add alternately the buttermilk and prunes.
Sift all together dry ingredients and add to remaining batter.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: little sugar cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs and lemon extract. Add sour cream, baking powder and the flour. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown around edges. Place raisin or M&M in center of each cake or sprinkle with colored sugar. Makes about 6 dozen little cakes.

title: new zealand pavlova
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Using an electric mixer, beat egg whites until stiff. Add water and beat again. Add sugar very gradually while still beating. Slow beater and add vinegar, vanilla and cornstarch.

Line an oven tray with baking paper. Draw a 9 inch circle on the baking paper. Spread the Pavlova to within 1 inch of the circle, keeping the shape as round and even as possible. Smooth top surface over. Bake Pavlova for 45 minutes, then leave to cool in the oven. Carefully lift Pavlova onto a serving plate. Decorate with whipped cream and fresh fruit, such as sliced kiwi fruit or strawberries. Serves 6.

title: apple roll
directions: Put the sugar and water in a 13 x 9-inch pan and set on stove until sugar is dissolved.
Mix dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Stir in enough milk for rolling consistency. Roll 1/2-inch thick, 6 x 12-inches.
Spread the apples on, plus butter and cinnamon. Roll up in
a long roll.
Pinch edges into roll to seal.
Slice 1 1/2-inches thick and quickly place slices, cut side down, in pan of boiling syrup. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 450° oven. Serve with nutmeg.

title: chowder(quantity)
directions: In a large frying pan, cook salt pork until well done.
Add onion and saute until golden.
While cooking this, cook potatoes in a 12-quart kettle.
Drain.
Add milk.
Stir flour into onion mixture.
When milk and potatoes are warm, thoroughly stir in thickening.
Immediately add corn or clams.
If making fish chowder, precook until fish breaks apart; then add.
Continue cooking until piping hot.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim steak of all fat and bone.
Cut into 1/2 x 4-inch strips. Brown strips slowly in margarine.
Add onion, mushrooms, salt, pepper and mustard.
Cook and brown until tender.
Add cream cheese and milk.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts and all is creamy. Serve over hot noodles.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Serves 6.

title: pan dandy cake(low in fat)
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, soda, salt and sugar in large bowl. Make a well and add oil, vinegar and vanilla. Pour water over all and blend. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Test with toothpick. Will make 3 dozen cupcakes.

title: fish sticks and cheese sandwich melts
directions: Prepare fish sticks according to box directions.
Spread tops of bread with butter.
Place 4 cooked fish sticks on bread, slice of cheese.
Then in a skillet over medium heat, place buttered side of bread down in pan.
Heat until golden brown and cheese is melted.

title: upside-down cake
directions: Combine the melted butter, pineapple and brown sugar in a skillet.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, stirring once.
Mix dressing in bowl.
Add potatoes and mix all together lightly.
Refrigerate.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Let dough rise for 2 hours.
Put in 3 pound coffee cans; let dough rise for 1 hour more.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package, using 1 1/2 cups milk. Add 1 cup of the marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Combine with pumpkin and seasonings.
Chill.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip (3/4 of large container) and remaining marshmallows. Spoon into dessert dishes; chill.
Garnish with additional topping.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; mix eggs and beat slightly.
Add to sugar and flour mixture.
Add milk, small amount at a time.
Cook in double boiler until thickened and add vanilla and butter.
Remove from heat and add coconut.
Put in prebaked pie crust and cool. Add Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut.

title: sangria(a spanish fruit punch)
directions: Mix orange juice, grape juice and sugar.
It's more like a "punch" if you let the drink freeze overnight and let it thaw a little so you will have something like a slushie.
Add the lemon, orange and apple and stir the next morning.
Enjoy!
Serves 8.

title: french carrots
directions: Put oil in 2-quart pan.
Add no water.
Add carrots, then onions over carrots.
Sprinkle sugar, salt and pepper over all. Add butter.
Cover and cook until tender on low heat.

title: donder's cake
directions: Mix well!
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° until done.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble into pie shell.
Arrange Swiss cheese over bacon.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix for at least 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake on lowest rack for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: blueberry muffins(makes 12)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk and vanilla. Mash 1/2 cup berries.
Stir into batter, along with 2 cups whole berries.

title: chicken-n-dressing
directions: Take boiled chicken off the bone; set aside.
Put cornbread and loaf bread in large bowl.
Add sage, onion and pepper.
Mix, then add chicken stock.
Stir; add cream of chicken.
Stir and add slightly beaten eggs.
Stir and add chicken to dressing mix.
Pour into an oblong greased pan or casserole dish.
Bake on 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cocktail cheese biscuits
directions: Cream the butter.
Add shredded cheese, then salt, pepper and flour.
Roll into small balls and press a pecan half on each to flatten.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Yields 40 to 50 biscuits.

title: 7-layer dip
directions: Use 9 x 9-inch dish. Layer bottom with the beans. Then working up in layers, add avocado dip, sour cream combined with 2 tablespoons taco mix, green onions, diced tomato, shredded cheese and top with black olives. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: obie's orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add orange sherbet while Jell-O is still warm.
Add drained pineapple chunks and drained mandarin oranges.
Add Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: pineapple-pecan upside-down cake(this is quick, because you start with mix.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles; rinse and drain well.
Butter a casserole dish. Combine noodles, tuna and soup.
Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle top with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together. Add water and yolks of eggs and cook until thick. Remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and raisins. Pour into a 9-inch baked pastry. Beat egg whites, adding 4 tablespoons sugar. Spread on pie and bake until brown on top, about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: favorite german chocolate pies
directions: Sprinkle coconut over bottom of pie shells.
Sprinkle pecans over coconut.
Combine sugar, cake flour and cornstarch in mixer bowl.
Add eggs, margarine and chocolate; beat until well blended. Add evaporated milk gradually, mixing constantly.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Spoon into prepared pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: red punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in large container.
May be frozen and thawed day before using.

title: sauerkraut cocoa cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: olde tyme sugar cookie recipe
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Roll to desired thickness.
Cut and bake at 325°.

title: quick punch
directions: Combine in a gallon jar.
Fill with water.
Pour over ice. Add 2 quarts of ginger ale and serve.
Serves 25 people.

title: pogo's light biscuits for belly-draggers
directions: Combine flours, cornmeal, brewer's yeast, powdered milk, parsley and garlic powder in bowl.
In small bowl dissolve dry yeast in warm water.
Stir well and add chicken stock.
Pour liquid mixture into dry ingredients.
Using hands, combine all ingredients, kneading several minutes.
Sprinkle additional cornmeal on board and roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into dog bone shapes and place on cookie sheet.
Brush lightly with egg glaze.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Let biscuits dry in oven several hours or overnight.
Store in airtight container.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: For each cookie, spread chocolate ready to spread frosting between two graham crackers.

title: baked spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Add tomato sauce soup and spices.
Cook spaghetti as directed; drain.
Add all preceding mixture to spaghetti.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-45 minutes.

title: chicken and snow pea pasta
directions: In a large saucepan, cook vermicelli to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain and keep warm.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix and chill day before use.
Green grapes can be used instead of purple grapes (which need to be halved and seeded). Leave red peel on apples.
Lemon juice keeps apples from turning brown.

title: newton sugar squares
directions: Cream butter with 1 cup sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and buttermilk; mix well.
Spread in greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan; sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Bake in (400°) hot oven for about 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in 40 cookies about 2-inch square.

title: moist brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, sour cream, salt, baking soda and eggs.
Bring margarine, cocoa and water to a boil in a saucepan.
Stir this into flour mixture until smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured 11 x 20 inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: peanut butter and white chocolate pretzels
directions: In a medium glass bowl, combine the peanut butter and white chocolate.
Microwave on Medium for 2 minutes.
Stir well. Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until the mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.

title: tangy italian cheese bread
directions: Place bread slices on a broiler rack.
Brush top side of each slice lightly with salad dressing.
Sprinkle cheeses, parsley and basil evenly over bread slices.
Broil 6 inches from heat until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and roll out on lightly floured board.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix butter, 1 egg and cake mix; spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine 3 eggs, vanilla, powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Pour this mixture over cake batter. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: rolled mints
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo syrup to 248°.
Add cream of tartar.
Remove from stove and pour over 1 egg white, well beaten, like divinity.
When thick and set up, add flavoring mint, winter green and coloring, if desired.
Drop large spoonfuls onto powdered sugar.
Roll around, flatten out with rolling pin and then roll in rolls like a jelly roll.
Break into pieces when set up or cut with scissors.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling salted water 6 to 8 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Combine eggplant, milk, soup, egg, onion, 3/4 cup stuffing mix and salt, stirring well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup stuffing mix and butter.
Sprinkle over eggplant mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: swedish hot dog potatoes
directions: Slice Big Franks and saute them with onion and margarine for a few minutes.
Add sliced potatoes together with tomato puree and cream.
Cover pan and cook a few more minutes.
Put in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ella's meat loaf
directions: Cook loaf with a lid at 350° for 45 minutes.
Then remove lid and continue cooking at 350° for 15 minutes longer.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Chill milk. Beat well.
Add lemonade directly from freezer and beat until thick.
Fold in thawed whipped topping.
Pour into pie crust and chill.
Wonderful on a hot summer night!

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Prepare & bake cake mix as directed on pkg.
When cake is still warm, but not hot, poke holes about 1 inch apart, using the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake and the caramel topping over the cake.
Refrigerate until completely cooled, about 1 hour.
Top with whipped topping and crushed Heath bars.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar or Sugar Twin, butter, buttermilk and coconut together in bowl.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: chewy pecan pie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly. Press into bottom of pan. Bake 20 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift sugar, cocoa, flour and soda into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan, then add remaining ingredients.
Stir well in pan until free from lumps.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Slice onion, potatoes and cheese.
Place ingredients in layers into buttered baking dish as follows:
beef, onion, potatoes, beans and cheese, ending with a layer of beef on top.
Cover with soup and bake in 350° oven until potatoes are brown.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, 1 1/3 cups instant puffs (dry), egg, salt, pepper, onion, catsup and milk.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 1 1/2-inch pie pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coffee apple bars
directions: In saucepan, combine raisins, water and coffee crystals; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Cream shortening and brown sugar until fluffy; blend in egg and vanilla. Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add alternately with raisins to creamed
mixture; mix well.
Stir in apples.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: turkey-vegetable loaf
directions: Combine contents of vegetable/seasoning packet and broth in large saucepan.
Add butter and vegetables.
Bring to a boil, separating vegetables with a fork.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 6 minutes.
Add stuffing crumbs and stir just to moisten.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add turkey and eggs and mix well.
Spoon into well-greased 9 x 5-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: outstanding white chili
directions: Place beans in heavy large pot.
Add enough cold water to cover by at least 3-inches and soak overnight.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients in blender and chill.
Serve on crackers.

title: funfetti cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and eggs. Stir by hand until thoroughly moistened. Shape dough in inch balls. Place on cookie sheet and flatten with floured hand. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes. Remove and spread with Funfetti frosting. Use the sprinkles to top each cookie after icing.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Put aside 1/2 bag of Dorito chips. Crush remaining chips. Put crushed chips in 9 x 12 casserole with grated onion and garlic powder.

title: oregon marinated salmon steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Place salmon steaks in marinate.
Cover and refrigerate twelve hours. Broil 8 minutes.

title: hearty winter soup
directions: Bring water, potatoes, carrots, and celery to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; cook, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted. Yields 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: chicken wings
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil.
Pour over chicken wings. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: green beans and tomatoes
directions: Saute beef, onion and pepper until brown.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and green beans; simmer about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: locrios(basic yellow rice-dominican republic style)
directions: Saute all ingredients, except rice and tomato paste and salt until golden brown.
Add rice, tomato paste and salt.
Mix together and fry 3 minutes more.
Add enough hot water to cover up to 1 1/2-inches above rice.
Add partially cooked meat and bring to a rapid boil until water is nearly absorbed.

title: dreamy fudge
directions: Put sugar, cocoa and milk in pot.
Let cook until it hardens around sides of pot.
Add butter, vanilla and peanut butter or nuts.
Put in buttered platter.

title: company's coming chicken breasts
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper. Brown in oil in a heavy skillet. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Combine soup, mushrooms, artichokes, sour cream and wine, pour over chicken. Bake uncovered at 350°F for one hour.
Serves 8.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Peel peaches and slice thinly.
Pour sugar and spices over peaches and stir.
Partially bake crust to avoid sogginess.
Pour filling in bottom crust and cut butter in pats on top of mixture. Add crust on top and bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: fruit and fiber muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine cereal and milk in bowl and let stand about 3 minutes.
Stir well.
Stir in egg whites and oil; add to flour mixture and mix just enough to moisten flour.
Fill greased muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Combine pudding, whipped topping and pecans in a bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in marshmallows, apples and pecans.
Chill until serving time.

title: brittany's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
In a bowl, beat butter and shortening on medium speed of electric mixer for 30 seconds. Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well combined.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop from a teaspoon 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
Remove; cool.
Makes about 72.

title: instant spiced punch
directions: To drink, add
2 teaspoons dry mixture to boiling water and sweeten to taste.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Blend soup and 1/2 can water.
Add allspice.
Measure out 1/4 cup soup mixture; set aside.
Combine crumbs, hamburg, egg, onion, parsley and salt.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch diameter balls.
In large skillet, brown meatballs in 1 tablespoon shortening or oil. Add to remaining soup mix the 1/2 tablespoon minced dill pickle (or sweet relish optional).
Cook over low heat 20 minutes, stirring now and then.
Serves 4.

title: cookies(banana or applesauce)
directions: Mash bananas and add dates and oil.
Mix with fork.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well and let stand for 3 minutes.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Store in icebox.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Heat walnuts in moderate 375° oven for 5 minutes, stirring once.
Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.

title: van's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix with your hands the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
This is too soft to mix with a mixer.
Add eggs, vanilla and peanut butter.
Now you can use the mixer.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Scoop out with a spoon (or ice cream scoop).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
This is an approximate time!
Also can:

title: crystallized peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan over medium heat. Add peanuts; cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until peanuts are coated and no syrup remains. Pour and spread over ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 275° for 30 minutes, stirring at 5 minute intervals.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie shell.

title: exotic turkey salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients, add mayonnaise, mix well.
Serve chilled on a bed of lettuce.

title: apricot bars
directions: Rinse apricots and boil for 10 minutes; drain.
Cool.
Chop into fine pieces.
In small bowl, mix margarine, sugar and 1 cup flour until crumbly.
In greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, pat mixture down and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sift together 1/3 cup flour, baking powder and salt; then mix on low speed, brown sugar and eggs.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in vanilla, apricots and nuts.
Spread over semi-cooled baked layer and bake 30 minutes longer at 350°.
Cool completely; cut into 1 x 2-inch strips and dust with powdered sugar.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer sugar, coffee and water for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.
Add vanilla and vodka.
It is now ready to drink.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk, vanilla and melted butter.
Pour peaches in baking dish.
Pour mixture on top.
Bake at 275° to 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: orange and pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Heat juice and mix orange juice with jello. Then cool and fold in mandarin oranges, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Then freeze.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Prepare noodles as directed.
Brown beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer.
Drain noodles.
In baking dish, layer meat, noodles and cheese to the top.
Meat should be on top.
Pour can of mushroom soup on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: scrambled egg souffle
directions: Oil 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put cubed bread in bottom; add cheese, either crumbled bacon, ham or sausage.
Add milk to beaten eggs, pour over all and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 4.

title: "s o s"
directions: Braise beef in frypan.
Make gravy in separate pan by melting butter and adding milk.
Slowly add flour, stirring constantly until thoroughly blended.
Stir in beef stock and add braised beef.
Add salt and pepper and chopped onion, if desired.
Simmer until tender.
Serve over toast or mashed potatoes.
Serves 4 or 2 hungry Marines!

title: evelyn's white sugar cookies
directions: *May also use combination of 3/4 cup butter and 1/4 cup margarine or Crisco.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well; bring to a boil.
Great for grilling meats.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and drain spinach and crisp in refrigerator.
Pour over spinach just before serving.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir in shortening mixture.

title: goof balls
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and vanilla to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter, mixing well.
Pour over cereal; fold together.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: baked red snapper("great company dish")
directions: Melt butter.
Add celery, onion and green pepper; simmer 15 minutes.
When celery is tender, add remaining ingredients (except snapper).

title: clinton's chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda on waxed paper.
Set aside.
Mix shortening, sugars and vanilla with an electric mixer until creamy.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and oats.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by well-rounded teaspoonful onto a greased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove baking sheet to a wire rack for 2 minutes before removing cookies.
Remove cookies onto a wire rack to cool completely.
Makes approximately 7 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: marguerite's gooseberry custard pie
directions: Place the 2 cups of gooseberries in the unbaked pie shell. Beat the egg and add the sugar and a small amount of milk.
Pour over berries and bake at 425°.
Turn oven down to 325° about the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: jane's meat and noodles
directions: In large, greased casserole, whisk together soups, seasonings, wine and water.
Fold in meat and mushrooms.
Cover tightly and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
Add a little more water if gravy becomes too thick.
Serve over buttered, parsleyed noodles.
Makes 8 servings.

title: kraut and wieners
directions: On top of stove put butter in pan and brown sliced wieners.
If too much butter left in pan, drain off.
Open kraut and drain off all water.
Add kraut to wieners and heat through and through.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind tomatoes, cabbage, bell pepper and onions.
Put in an earthenware jar.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Pour pineapple into bowl, juice and all.
Mix in dry pudding; stir until dissolved.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows.
Mix together.

title: dressing for banana salad
directions: Mix all together, except bananas and peanuts. Cook, stirring it often until it boils well.
Then remove from stove and cool.
Can cook dressing ahead of time and store in the refrigerator until ready for use.
After it is cooled, add the bananas and chopped cocktail peanuts.
Serve immediately after adding these to the dressing.

title: burrito pie
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan with vegetable spray.
Lay 2 tortillas in pan (they will overlap).
Spread 1/2 of 1 can of refried beans over tortillas.
Spread 1/4 of jar of picante sauce on beans.
Sprinkle 1/4 of cheese over sauce.
Repeat layers 3 times.
Place 2 tortillas on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
When serving, top with sour cream, if desired.
Good with nacho chips and a tossed salad. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Place undrained beans in a large kettle or saucepan; mash about 2/3 of the beans and leave the rest whole.
Add salt, garlic, pepper, oil and parsley, stirring well.
Then add all the vegetables, butter, tomatoes and water or broth.
Simmer 1 hour or more and then add sherry.
If desired, macaroni may be added at this time.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with freshly grated Parmesan cheese before serving.
If soup seems too thick, add more water.

title: oatmeal quickies
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir together cocoa and sugar in small bowl.
Add milk to cocoa mixture.
Add cocoa mixture to butter (melted) and boil for 1 minute.
In large bowl combine oatmeal, salt and peanut butter.
Add cocoa mixture and add vanilla.
Stir all together and drop onto wax paper by teaspoons.
Let cool.

title: spinach salad
directions: Stir together first 9 ingredients.
Pour over cleaned spinach (tough stems removed).
Add crumbled bacon.
Toss well.
Sauce can be made in advance.
Serves 6.
(Mushrooms, purple onion and cherry tomato are good additions.)

title: zucchini banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together soup, dry mustard, salt, milk and eggs.
Layer in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish:
bread, sausage, mixture and cheese, then repeat.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Heat milk until boiling; pour in 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Add bread cubes; allow to set 15 minutes.
Beat eggs and add spices.
Mix with bread and milk; cover pan.
Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Contains 4 ounces protein, 2 breads, 2 milks, 2 fruits.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine ingredients and stir well.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Turn once and drain and serve hot.
This can be and is better to mix up the night before or at least a few hours before.

title: congealed blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add pie filling and pineapple.
Let stand overnight.
Soften cream cheese; mix in sugar, vanilla, sour cream and nuts.
Whip.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well and pour into 4 greased coffee cans, filling one-half full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans.
Wrap in foil.
Can be frozen.

title: doughnuts
directions: Blend sugar and eggs.
Add potatoes which have been mashed and thinned with water.
Add oil and salt, then warm milk.
Lastly, add yeast and flour.
Set in warm place and let raise until double in size.
Then roll and cut with doughnut cutter.
Let raise again. Fry in hot lard or Crisco at 350° or 375°.
Shake in a bag of 10x sugar or cinnamon and granular sugar.

title: ruby slippers
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs in large bowl.
Blend together and then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes until creamy. Spoon 1/3 of batter into well-greased and floured cake pan. Sprinkle with half of Jell-O.
Repeat layers.
Spread remaining batter over gelatin to cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool on rack and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Drain carrots.
Cook onions in butter.
Add soup and cheese and mix with carrots.
Put in greased casserole.
Toss stuffing and butter and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Beat cream cheese with fork (we did it 1/2 of cheese at a time so we could make different colors).
Add mint flavor and coloring before sugar.
Add powdered sugar a little at a time, beating well after each addition.
Use all the sugar.
Must be kneaded with hands at the last as it is very stiff.
Wrap dough in waxed paper so it won't dry out.
Pinch of small pieces to fit plastic molds. Dip in granulated sugar.
Press in molds; take off excess around edges.
Push out of mold on waxed paper; let dry.
Makes 2 or 3 dozen.

title: i can't believe they're cookies
directions: Mix all together well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Flatten with greased, sugared glass bottom.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese and dressing. Roll into ball and roll in Bacos. Serve with crackers of chips.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in small amount of water until tender.
Debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook spaghetti in bouillon and water.
Do not drain water.
Add onion, green pepper and any other seasonings desired.
Mix noodles and chicken.
If too much water, drain some.
Add cheese and heat until melted.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Slice each chicken breast horizontally to form a pocket.
Brush each ham slice with honey mustard and fold in half.
Fold a cheese slice around each ham slice.
Insert in pocket of chicken and secure with toothpick. Melt butter in a large skillet over med-hi heat.
Cook chicken in butter until browned, about 4 minutes per side.
Arrange chicken on a rack in a baking pan.
Bake chicken until an instant- read thermometer inserted in center of the meat registers 180°, about 15 - 20 minutes.

title: down in the hollow french toast
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, salt and milk.
Stir in Jack Daniels whiskey.
Dip bread slices in mixture.
Melt butter in hot skillet.
Brown each side of bread.
Serve hot, sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Yields 2 servings.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: lemon and herb chicken
directions: Rub chicken with the
cut
half
of
the onion; discard onion. Mix herbs and garlic
with
lemon juice and olive oil. Add chicken, turning to
coat
with marinade.
Marinate for 30 minutes.
To marinate more than 1 hour, cover and refrigerate.

title: grape fizzle
directions: Put the ice cubes into a glass.
Squeeze the piece of lemon into the glass.
Fill the glass half full of ginger ale.
Slowly pour grape juice into the glass until full.
Yields 1 serving.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Roll candy and dates in part of flour sifted for cake.
Add remaining flour to egg and butter mixture, alternating with milk.
Add coconut, candy, dates and nuts.
Place mixture in tube pan and bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: sweet sour fruit salad
directions: Fill large salad bowl half full of sliced lettuce.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, butter, Crisco and oil together.
Sift together salt, soda, cream of tartar and flour; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Roll in balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy no roll pie crust
directions: Combine all dry ingredients together.
Pour in oil and milk. Stir to form a dough.
Press into pie plate.
Very flaky.

title: texas cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and drop onto a greased cookie sheet with a tsp.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on a rack for best results.

title: mom's date pudding
directions: Bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick.
Add corn syrup, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: green bean salad
directions: Heat the sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper and pour over the vegetables while hot, then refrigerate.

title: grilled chicken livers
directions: Wrap slices of bacon around liver.
Hold in place with toothpicks.
Marinate in sauce 30 minutes.
Cook on grill until done.

title: corn puddin
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine corn, well beaten egg, sugar, salt and pepper.
To this, add 1/2 of margarine (melted) and sprinkle flour into mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and dot with rest of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: reese's brownies cupcakes
directions: Mix brownie mix with 1 extra egg.
Pour into cupcake bake cups, 1/2 filled.
Unwrap Reese's and drop into middle of cupcake. Bake as directed for brownies on box.

title: save-a-penny casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Stir in soup, spaghetti and vegetables.
Put in ungreased 11 x 17
x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and let stand until melted. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss apples in lemon juice to prevent browning of fruit.
Mix apples, marshmallows, walnuts and celery.
Add enough mayo, yogurt or Cool Whip to moisten ingredients (about 1/2 cup).
Toss lightly.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar with electric mixer. Add peanut butter and mix, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust and chill for about 2 hours.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix baking soda and buttermilk together and set aside.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in butter; add raisins and caraway seed. Add buttermilk with soda mixture to dry ingredients slowly; mix while adding.
You may add more raisins, if you desire.
Grease and flour a round baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes to an hour, until done.
Should be golden brown when tester comes out clean.

title: crockpot macaroni and cheese
directions: Stir into crockpot, Cook on lowest heat for 3 hours. Add extra cup of milk & stir, if needed.

title: armenian cake
directions: Mix with knives the brown sugar, flour and butter.
Place half in a 9 x 13-inch pan and pat.
To other half, add remaining ingredients (except nuts and cinnamon).
Pour on top.
Sprinkle with nuts and cinnamon.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool completely before cutting.
Bottom crust will be crisp.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: Season pork chops and brown in electric skillet.
When brown on both sides, take out and put aside.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini to maintain crispness and drain.
Saute onion. Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish or a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes completely.
Saute onions in margarine until tender in small saucepan.
Add cream of mushroom soup and sour cream; stir over medium heat until begins to bubble.
Place thawed potatoes and mushrooms in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on salt. Pour mixture over the top.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Cook noodles in broth.
After noodles are cooked, add sour cream and cream of mushroom soup. Mix all together.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle with Ritz crackers.
Squeeze butter over top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel corn or popcorn balls
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to rolling boil.
Then boil 2 minutes longer.
Pour over 1 gallon of popped popcorn and mix. Shape into balls, if desired.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix well all above ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan.

title: lemon cheesecake cookies
directions: Line an 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil, extending 2-inches beyond 2 sides of the pan.
Grate 1 teaspoon lemon zest and squeeze 3 tablespoons lemon juice from it.
Beat butter, salt, 1/2 teaspoon lemon zest and 1/4 cup sugar until creamy.
Beat in flour until crumbly.
Beat in about 1 teaspoon of juice until dough holds together.
Press dough into bottom of lined pan and refrigerate 15 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with Baker's Joy.
Spread coconut and pecans on bottom.
Mix cake as box says and pour over nuts and coconut.
Melt oleo.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar to the melted oleo.
Mix well and spread over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
This cake is not pretty, but it is delicious.

title: herbed baby potatoes
directions: Scrub red potatoes, unpeeled and quartered.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, toss potatoes in oil to coat each piece.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss again to coat evenly.
Pepper to taste.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until lightly brown and fork-tender.
Serves 6.

title: 7 layer taco dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning; set aside. Layer in the following order: bean dip, avocado dip, mayonnaise mixture, green onions, Cheddar cheese, Monterey Jack cheese and olives.

title: mrs. t. h. hinote's honey pecan pie
directions: Mix honey and beaten eggs.
Stir flour in water until mixture is smooth.
Mix with honey and eggs.
Add pecans, vanilla and butter.
Pour in baked pie shell. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until firm.

title: lime salad
directions: Drain juice off pineapple and add it to water to make 2 cups liquid.
Combine with other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: good pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and margarine together.
Add sugar, then 1 egg at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to batter alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Set in cold oven; turn oven to 375° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and cook for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Boil spaghetti; drain.
Mix in Parmesan cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Brown chopped onion, chopped green pepper and ground beef. Drain and mix with spaghetti sauce, plus oregano and garlic.

title: party punch
directions: Bring to boil water and sugar.
Cool.
Add Kool-Aid, orange juice (frozen) and frozen lemonade.
Then add 2 quarts of cold water, then the pineapple juice.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine preserves, jelly, pepper, mustard and horseradish; blend
well.
Refrigerate;
when
ready to serve, spread sauce over
cream
cheese.
Serve
with crackers.
Sauce will keep weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
(Can sprinkle toasted sesame seed or almonds on top.)

title: apple julep
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Chill.
Garnish with mint leaves.
Yields 7 1/4 cups, 120 calories per cup.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Pour pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, cinnamon, sugar, nutmeg, cloves and salt into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top, then chopped pecans.
Drizzle oleo over the top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients, except milk.
Add enough milk to mix good, but leave sort of thick. Drop from teaspoon into hot grease.
Cook until golden brown.

title: aunt peggy's marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; slice larger ones.
Place mushrooms and onion slices in a pretty bowl.
Pour 1/2 of dressing over them.
Marinate for at least 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt margarine in heavy boiler.
Saute onion and celery slightly.
Then add cubes of potatoes.
Cover and cook over low fire 10 to 15 minutes, then add to pot 3 cups water, Pet milk, ham, soup, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Continue to cook on low fire for 30 minutes.

title: curried broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Combine with bacon, raisins, onions and nuts.
In small bowl mix remaining ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Pour over broccoli mixture and toss.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: sun cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Makes a large moist cake.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, Veg-All, cream of chicken soup and broth all together.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Mix oleo, flour and milk.
Pour over casserole mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; set aside.
Beat butter in mixer bowl until light.
Gradually add sugars and continue beating until very light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine milk, rum and vanilla; add to batter alternately with dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 30 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in heavy skillet, cooking until done. Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or may be microwaved on High power until well heated (about 15 minutes, stirring about halfway through cooking).

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Slowly add sugar.
Add beaten eggs. Sift flour and baking powder together and add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk and flavorings.
Beat for 5 minutes and pour into prepared 9-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly and rub skins with oil; bake for 1 hour or until done (or microwave).
Let cool to the touch.
Slice skin away from top of each potato; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Mash pulp; stir in butter and next 6 ingredients.
Spoon potato mixture into shells.
Top with marshmallows and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: pie filling cake
directions: Fold all ingredients gently with a spatula.
Do not beat!!! Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: quick caramel icing
directions: Melt margarine over low heat for 1 minute.
Remove and add brown sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Boil for 1 minute while stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add milk and return to boil for another 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.
Spread over your favorite cake.

title: yam and marshmallow bake
directions: Drain yams and mash.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add juice to yams with sugar and butter.
Beat well.
Stir in pineapple and pecans.
Coat inside of 9-inch pie plate with no-stick cooking spray.
Spoon in yam mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix buttermilk or sour milk with bran and let set while mixing everything else.
Then combine the two mixtures.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 12.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly with mixer.
Add sugar and syrup; continue beating.
Add salt, vanilla and melted butter to mixture.
Place pecans in bottom of pie crust.
Add prepared filling to pie shell. Cover edge of crust with foil during the first 15 minutes of baking.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until the center of the pie shakes slightly when moved.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and egg well.
Add chocolate chips if desired.
Drop in desired size.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: old fashion beef stew
directions: Cover with water.
Cook for 2 hours and it's ready to eat.

title: hash brown casserole #2
directions: Place hash browns in oblong dish.
Mix cheese, onions, chicken soup, salt, 1/2 stick melted butter and sour cream together and pour over hash browns.
About 5 to 10 minutes before it is done, pour 2 cups of corn flakes over the top and drizzle 1/2 stick melted butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening. Beat up the egg in a cup; add the vinegar and fill the cup to 1 cup mark with water. Add the amount of water mixture needed for the flour. This can be rolled and re-rolled and have good texture. Good for beginners.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour in ice cream freezer.

title: congealed blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine juices of the blueberries and, if necessary, add enough water to make 1 cup. Add the juice to the gelatin mixture.
Now stir in drained fruit. Pour into a 2-quart flat pan.
Let stand in refrigerator until firm.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Grind onions and peppers.
Heat sugar, salt and vinegar to boiling.
Add onion and peppers.
Cook 3 minutes only.
Fill sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain the spinach well and mix with ingredients.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: baked stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Arrange caps, hollow side up, in a shallow baking dish.
Chop stems and in a small bowl, mix stems with the pecans, parsley, butter, garlic, thyme, salt and pepper.
Heap into the mushroom caps.
Pour the cream over the mushrooms and bake 20 minutes, basting with the cream a couple of times.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Mix and pour over vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, pepper, celery and mushrooms).
Serve cold.

title: crispy chocolate chip cereal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together first 5 ingredients. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Add sifted ingredients to the creamed ingredients.
Mix in oatmeal, Triples, walnuts, chocolate chips and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
For chewy cookies, drop by tablespoonfuls.
Yields approximately 8 dozen cookies.

title: quick orange salad
directions: Mix and it is ready to serve.
Also good with peaches and peach jello.

title: beets polynesian
directions: In a saucepan, combine the brown sugar, flour and salt; stir in vinegar and 3/4 cup water.
Add the undrained pineapple, raisins and butter or margarine.
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Stir in drained beets.
Heat through.
Makes 10 servings.

title: aspic with everything
directions: Heat tomato juice, sugar and salt.
Dissolve jello in tomato juice mixture over heat, stirring until blended.
Add ketchup. When partially jelled in refrigerator, add remaining ingredients. Pour into slightly oiled 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Chill until serving time. Serves 20 to 24.

title: beef burgers
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 1/2 hour before serving on buns. This will feed a large family or keeps well in the refrigerator if family is small.

title: no peek stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a 3 to 5-quart baking dish. Cover; bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Do not peek!! Yields 6 servings.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream butter and part of sugar.
Add egg yolks and rest of sugar and cream well.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk.
Add vanilla and prunes.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Pour into 2 wax-paper lined, 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Ice with Mocha Icing.

title: fast tortillas
directions: Combine flour and Bisquick and enough water to make a dry dough.
Knead for about 5 minutes.
Knead into a ball and cover with dry towel for about 10 minutes.
Squeeze balls of dough and knead into flat balls.
Roll with a rolling pin, turning dough so outcome will be round tortillas.
Place on griddle or frying pan heated at medium heat.
Check in 3 or 4 minutes and turn if ready. When done, place cooked tortilla on towel to cool slightly.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix egg and sugar; add peanut butter.
Form cookies.
Bake 10 minutes exactly on ungreased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: connie's caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat for 2 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add milk.
Stir until it reaches boiling point again.
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat in powdered sugar.
Spread over cooled Connie's Crazy Chocolate Cake.

title: cheese and ham rolls
directions: Blend mayonnaise, cream cheese and mustard; add olives. Spread this mixture about 1/8-inch thick over the ham slices. Roll up the ham like a jelly roll; fasten with toothpicks.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Slice rolls in 1/4-inch slices and serve on small round crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookie(mix in a jar)
directions: To make mix: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl.
Place mixture in a 1-quart jar.
Layer remaining ingredients in the order listed, pressing down firmly after each layer.
Seal with a lid and decorate with fabric and ribbon.
All of the mixes in a jar are great gifts for teachers, friends, etc.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend in small bowl all ingredients. Trim cauliflower of leaves and cut core to allow head to sit on it.
Spread butter mixture evenly over head.
Sit head upright in casserole dish and cover with foil tightly.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours. Serve whole.
Spoon juices over it.

title: diet dressing
directions: Combine salad oil, lemon juice, water, salt, ketchup, mustard, paprika and Worcestershire sauce.
Beat with rotary beater until well mixed.
Chill in a tightly covered jar.
Mix well before serving.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: candy cookies
directions: Blend oleo, brown sugar, granulated sugar, salt, eggs, soda, cinnamon and cut up candy bars and add to mix.
Add chocolate chips, coconut and oatmeal; blend well.
Then add flour.
Mix well. Spoon out on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk and sugar.
Boil 5 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add all remaining ingredients except walnuts.
Stir until mixed well.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: flaky paste
directions: Sift flour and salt together into a bowl; chop in the shortening with a knife until well mixed with the flour.
Add ice cold water to form a dough, cutting and mixing the paste thoroughly while adding the water.

Flour a board and roll the paste out thinly, rolling only lengthwise and keeping the edges straight, then fold evenly into three layers (lengthwise as a sheet of paper would be folded to fit into a business envelope).
Turn it half around and roll again.
Repeat the folding and rolling twice and chill the paste if possible before baking.
It is the folding and rolling that produce the flakes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Stir dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; blend well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: tuna dill sandwiches(prep time: 15 minutes)
directions: Stir together dressing, dill and pepper.
Add tuna and carrot; mix well.
For each sandwich, top one muffin half with lettuce, cheese and tuna mixture.
Garnish with fresh dill, if desired. Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: mrs. white's lemon pudding
directions: Blend sugar, flour, lemon juice and rind, salt, yolks and milk; beat well.
Fold in egg whites, beaten.
Pour into glass baking dish; set in hot water.
Bake for 1 hour in slow oven; cool.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.
This pudding is cakelike on top with thick, creamy sauce underneath.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix pumpkin pie mix, beaten eggs and milk and pour over cake mixture.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and margarine and add to 1 cup of cake mixture.
Sprinkle over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut pecans, orange slices and dates into small pieces.
Mix in flour well.
Cream in margarine, sugar and eggs. Mix soda in buttermilk; add to dry ingredients.
Bake in tube pan 3 hours at 250°.
Pierce top with toothpick when done.

title: christmas red punch
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat.
Stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat. Cool.
Pour mixture into a gallon jar and add pineapple juice.
Pour in enough water to make a gallon.
Freeze.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease well a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir for 2 minutes or until mixture is a smooth, thick batter.
Pour into prepared pan and bake until light brown on top, about 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned apple crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Add apple slices and mix until apples are evenly coated.
Spoon into pie shell.

title: swiss cheese chicken breast
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish. Cover with cheese slices. Combine soup and wine and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with crushed dressing mix and drizzle with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti bolognese
directions: Crumble beef into a 3-quart microproof casserole.
Add onion and garlic.
Place in microwave oven.
Cook on High 3 minutes. Stir to break up beef; drain.
Place in microwave oven.
Cook on High, 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except spaghetti. Cover. Cook on 50% power for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving over spaghetti.
Yields 10 servings.

title: pepper steak fajita
directions: Cut steak in long thin strips.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Fry a small amount at a time in oil (in wok), pushing to sides and putting more meat in as it cooks.
Drain off the juice as it cooks.
Stir-fry tomatoes, peppers and onions after removing meat to drain.
Do not overcook vegetables.
They will be crisp, drain off juice, add steak, lime juice, pepper sauce and water.
Gently stir and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with a slotted spoon over cooked white rice or on soft taco shells with cheese and taco sauce.

title: ginger peachy salad
directions: In bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice and ginger; toss with chicken, celery and grapes.
Chill.
Serve in peach halves arranged on salad greens.
Garnish with almonds.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: evelyn barr's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve sugar in water, boil 5 minutes.
Dissolve jello in hot syrup.
Cool.
Peel oranges and grind with apples and cranberries.
Add fruit to cooled jello mixture.
Mix thoroughly. Let cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 6 weeks.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Chill about one hour or bake at 375° for 6 to 9 minutes.

title: ricotta egg biscuits(it's a favorite holiday cookie!)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs, margarine, Ricotta and vanilla and mix with a wooden spoon.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool and frost with Drizzle Topping.

title: hospitality pineapple meatballs
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/2 cup syrup.
Place pineapple on paper towels.
Soak bread in water; squeeze out.
Mix bread thoroughly with beef, eggs and salt.
Shape into small balls, enclosing pineapple tidbits in each ball.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients until its of spread consistency.
Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and beat until thick.
Blend in dry ingredients thoroughly alternately with mashed bananas.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes in loaf pan (greased in the bottom).

title: easy ketchup
directions: Cook tomatoes, green pepper and onion; let drain overnight. Put pulp through sieve.
Add everything together; cook 10 minutes or longer until thick.

title: never fail pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, corn syrup, salt and vanilla.
Melt butter and add to this mixture.
Line pie shell with pecans.
Add on another layer of pecans and on sides of pie shell.
Add mixture slowly.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
The nuts will rise to the top and form a crusted layer.
Cool and eat.

title: low carb fudge(3 carbs)
directions: Beat all ingredients except nuts until smooth. Line 8 x 8 square pan with foil. Sprinkle nuts on the bottom and fudge on the top. Cover and freeze. Cut into 16 pieces.

title: bachelor's soup
directions: Cook ground beef in large saucepan.
Add V-8 and mixed vegetables.
Cook on medium to low for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce, eggs and hot water.
Sift flour and spices together 3 times.
Add to applesauce mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Grease and flour (also spray with Pam) a 10-inch tube pan. Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick can be removed clean.
Better than ordinary fruitcake recipe.

title: quick meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; pack in loaf pan and cook 1 hour.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine with milk, Cool Whip, pie filling, and nuts.
Chill until set.
Good as a salad or a dessert.

title: baked lasagna a la pearson
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper and celery medium fine.
Chop garlic. Heat olive oil in a pot over medium heat.
Add garlic to pot when oil is hot and stir until light brown.
Add remainder of seasonings and cook until tender, but not brown.

Add crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce and spices and continue to cook for 10 minutes. Add water or beef stock, Worcestershire sauce, 1 cup Romano cheese, salt and pepper and cook for 1 hour on a slow fire.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat cake mix, jello, cooking oil, water and eggs all together.
Bake in tube pan as directed on cake box.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and saute until tender; remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and next 6 ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Peel and devein shrimp.
Pour marinate over shrimp turning to coat both sides; chill for 1 hour.
Soak 4 (8-inch) wooden skewers in water for 30 minutes.
Place shrimp on skewers so shrimp lie flat.
Grill on medium hot coals 3 to 4 minutes on each side until shrimp turn pink.
Squeeze lemon over shrimp and serve.

title: butterscotch pudding cake
directions: Make up pudding as per instructions on box.
Empty spice cake mix into the pudding (recommend Duncan Hines, Pillsbury or Betty Crocker).
Mix well for a few minutes on low speed or by hand. Place mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: crisp sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Put lime in enough water to cover cucumbers in large pan and soak overnight.
Next day, wash cucumbers through 4 or 5 rinse waters.
Then soak cucumbers in ice water for 2 hours.
Cook vinegar, sugar, and spice bundle until boiling.
Add cucumbers and cook about 45 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Mix at low speed for 4 minutes.
Makes a large amount.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sharp cheese until melted. Add cottage cheese, cooked macaroni and tuna (broken up).
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: raspberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add enough water to raspberry juice to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Add to gelatin.
Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in sour cream and berries.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: ranch house biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix all dry ingredients together. Add oil and buttermilk to yeast.
Mix thoroughly.
Keep in refrigerator until needed.
Take out as much as you need to make a small batch.
Roll out as any other biscuits.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots in boiling water until tender; drain.
Saute bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Saute onions and celery in 2 tablespoons of bacon fat.
Combine cooked vegetables, bacon, salt, pepper, milk and half and half cream. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Do not boil.
Garnish with cheese and parsley.

title: deb's chicken casserole
directions: Crush crackers.
Add to melted butter; set aside.
Cook chicken; tear in bite size pieces.
Mix chicken, both soups, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Place 1/2 crackers on bottom of casserole.
Add the chicken mixture; sprinkle other 1/2 of crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seasoned meatballs
directions: *For each pound of hamburger.

title: crazy cake
directions: Beat margarine and 1 egg thoroughly and add 1 box Duncan Hines white or yellow cake mix, which has instant pudding included.
Mix until crumbly.

title: coconut pie in a flash
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend on medium for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Bake 450 degrees for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut...a lot of coconut...it's so easy.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly. Place in roaster and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: easy-does-it corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in large pot until golden.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook until softened.
Add corn and broth, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Makes 6 servings.

title: white trash
directions: Mix together cereal and roasted peanuts.
Microwave until melted, the chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Coat cereal/peanut mixture with melted chips, etc.
Place all in a large plastic bag containing a 1 to 2 pound box of powdered sugar. Shake, baby, shake.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans.
Beat all ingredients in large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for 45 seconds.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 50 or 60 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Butter the inside of a metal cake pan 8-inches wide and 3-inches deep.
Do not use a spring-form pan. Sprinkle the inside with graham cracker crumbs and shake the crumbs around the bottom and sides until coated.
Shake out the excess crumbs.
Set aside.

title: mexican soup a pollo
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add corn, return to boil; reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 5 more minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Add salsa and heat through.
Garnish with cheese.

title: violet jam
directions: Rinse violet blossoms well and place in a blender.
Add 3/4 cup water and lime juice; blend well.
Gradually add sugar, blending until a smooth paste is formed.
In a saucepan, combine pectin and remaining water; bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute. Add to blender and blend for 1 minute.
Quickly pour into prepared jars or glasses and seal.

title: jean's no sweat stew
directions: Place meat in 2-quart casserole dish with cover.
Place onions, carrots, celery over top of meat.
Add jar gravy, pour over meat and vegetables.
Add 1/4 jar of water.
Cover and bake in oven at 250° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice, noodles or potatoes.
(No sweat).

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream well together.
Add salad oil (about 2 teaspoons at a time).
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flavoring and salt.
Add milk and flour (mix baking powder in flour) alternately.
Beat well. Bake in a greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on cake rack.

title: gan gan's rice pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together.
Pour half of mixture into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese. Add rest of corn mixture and rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese basil linguini
directions: In four-quart bowl, combine tomatoes, cream cheese, oil, vinegar and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Cover and marinate at room temperature for at least 2 hours.
Cook pasta as directed on package; al dente is best.
Drain.
Add pasta to marinated mixture and toss lightly.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon sheet cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the cake mix and eggs until well blended.
Fold in pie filling.
Spread into a greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 18-20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. cool on a wire rack.
In a small mixing bowl beat cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread over cake, store in the refrigerator.
Yield:
30-35 servings.

title: carolina apple pudding
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart casserole.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in bowl.
Mix well.
Add milk and butter.
Pour batter into 2-quart casserole.
Drain apples, put in center of batter.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until batter covers fruit and crust browns.
Serve warm.

title: cheese and sausage puffs
directions: For immediate use:
Combine all ingredients, drop walnut size on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms(funghi crudi di marinati)
directions: Clean and dry mushrooms;
cut into slices.
In a shaker jar combine olive oil,
salt,
ground
pepper,
garlic,
lemon juice, crushed pepper and
oregano.
Mix well and pour mixture over mushrooms.
Toss.
Let
mixture
