marinate at least 1 hour before serving, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. This is a great addition to antipasto.

title: grilled flank steak
directions: Place flank steak in a large shallow dish.
Combine wine and next 5 ingredients and pour over.
Cover dish and refrigerate overnight.
Drain steak.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Grill.

title: rum sauce for bread pudding
directions: Place
milk, butter and sugar in saucepan.
Let come to a boil.
Thicken
with
roux	made
of 1 tablespoon oil and 2 tablespoons
flour.
Remove
from heat and add nutmeg, vanilla and rum flavoring to taste.
Serve over bread pudding.

title: 4 layer chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and finely chopped pecans well and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°. Cool.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Stir-fry chicken, onion and pepper in oil until chicken is thoroughly cooked.
Add corn, broth and salsa; bring to a boil. Stir in rice and cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: peanut butter oatmeal refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter and margarine together until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Beat well.
Add rolled oats and raisins.
Shape dough into a long roll, about 2-inches across.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice into 1/8-inch thick slices with sharp knife. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix and simmer 15 minutes. Dot ham with cloves and spoon glaze on ham.

title: kirk link's ozark puddin' pie
directions: Beat egg and sugar until smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add nuts, apples and vanilla. Bake in greased pie pan, 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Add oil and milk. Stir with a fork.
Gather dough into a ball and roll out to fit a 9-inch pie pan.
Put in pan and press edges to rim of pan and flute.
Pour in any filling and bake.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat together pumpkin, eggs and milk.
Add sugar and spices. Beat again.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over pumpkin mix.
Spoon melted margarine over all, then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until knife comes out clean.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: potato "omelet"
directions: Grate potatoes and place in a bowl of cold water.
Butter frying pan.
Take a handful of grated potatoes.
Squeeze out the excess water and spread evenly on the bottom of pan.
Sprinkle a pinch of salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low heat until potatoes are tender and hold together.
Flip over.
Cover and cook until bottom is golden brown.
Cover omelet with tomato slice and grated cheese.
Let cheese melt, then add spinach leaf.
Serve warm.

title: cherry jewels
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk, lemon juice, orange juice, lemon rind and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually blend in flour.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll into balls; roll in nuts.
Make indentation in the top and fill with jelly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cashew crunch
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat butter and sugar.
Remove from heat and add syrup and water to the mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until mixture reaches 290°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cashews.
Pour onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: mother's date-nut loaf
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and let stand 10 minutes. Meanwhile add the sugar gradually to the egg while beating.
Add baking powder, soda and salt.
Then add dates and water.
Stir. Add flour, shortening, nuts and vanilla.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° 45-50 minutes.

title: sweet rice o tel
directions: Follow directions on package for cooking rice.
Add ground beef and onion after having browned them together.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add sugar, salt and pepper the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: fruit in cones
directions: Fill each cone with 3/4 cup fruit (enough to fill rim). Drizzle with honey.
Sprinkle with granola.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise just scrub and rinse them.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them open slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Better if able to set for awhile (hour or so).

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Next mix the cold water, sugar, pineapple juice, lemon juice and cherries. Add to jello mixture. Stir well. Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serves about 25.

title: diabetic banana-oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine bananas, oil, eggs, sweetener and vanilla.
Blend well. Add dry ingredients and raisins.
Mix until moistened.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased shiny cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake until golden brown at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut into finger size pieces.
Should be served slightly warm.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add condensed milk, Cool Whip and vanilla to pudding mix.
Make layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Top with Cool Whip or vanilla wafers.
Cover and let chill in refrigerator.

title: cheesy chicken corn chowder
directions: In a saucepan, combine chicken, onion, celery and 1/2 cup water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken; cut off meat and chop.
Discard skins and bones.
Return meat to broth; stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a saucepan, mix the cocoa, sugar, flour and salt.
Add water. Cook until thickened.
Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla. Blend in.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done (about 1 hour).
Let cool, then pick off bone.
Bring broth to a boil.
Beat eggs in a bowl; add water, broth and salt to eggs.
Then add enough flour to thicken.
Roll out thin and cut.
Drop dumplings in boiling broth.
Add chicken.

title: tex-mex lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in canned tomatoes and taco seasoning.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Place in a greased or Pam-sprayed casserole.
Slice cheese over broccoli.
Melt margarine and mix with crumbs.
Spread evenly on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, just long enough to heat, melt cheese and brown the crumbs a bit.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Cut bread into circles with a cookie cutter.
Spread with cheese or peanut butter.
Decorate with dots or fruit or vegetable nuts.
Slice hard-boiled eggs or tiny shapes of cheese.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Stir dry ingredients together, cut in shortening, add yeast and buttermilk. Knead dough until it holds together. Roll dough to 3/4 inch thick. Cut out, then fold in half. Bake at 400 for 15-20 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together Ricotta cheese, spinach and Parmesan cheese until well blended.
Layer 1 cup sauce, three noodles, 1 cup Ricotta cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers 2 to 3 times.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking for 15 minutes. Let stand about 5 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: salmon stew
directions: Fry onion in bacon grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly on low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate dip
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add cream, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix well. Keep warm in fondue pot.
Dip fruit.

title: blueberry icebox pie
directions: Melt butter; mix well with other ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.

title: anisette-rum cake
directions: Make puddings according to package directions.
Split sponge biscuits in half and line the bottom of a 12 x 10 x 12-inch baking dish with one layer of split biscuits.
Spread layer of vanilla pudding over biscuits.
Top with another layer of chocolate pudding.
Chill, then spread Cool Whip over top.
Garnish with sliced almonds.
Can sprinkle rum over biscuit slices before adding pudding if desired.
Serves 12.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except margarine. Melt margarine in baking pan that will be used in baking the casserole. Stir melted margarine into corn mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion for 10 minutes in water; add drained corn, green beans, peas and corned beef.
Cook 10 minutes. Drain off excess water.
Add juice to cover vegetables.
Heat just enough to get juice hot.

title: richly divine cappuccino wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter. Mix in sugar, then egg. Add vanilla and instant coffee crystals. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Mix into butter mixture. Stir in chocolate chips. Spoon into greased 9-inch round cake pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Cool slightly and cut into slender pie-shaped wedges. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice, bell pepper and onion. Mix rice mixture, Cheddar and cottage cheese and sour cream in casserole dish. Bake approximately 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all together until it comes to a soft ball.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch. Add water and cook until clear.
Add strawberry Jell-O and cool. Add fresh strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: huge winter chili recipe
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add vegetables and seasoning.
Brown. Add 5 cans of beans and tomatoes.
Add enough water to rinse your cans and fill a 22-quart pan.
Yield:
22-quarts plus.
Store in garage in winter!

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix together and beat.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: grasshopper punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 9 cups boiling water.
Bring sugar and 4 cups of water to a quick boil; add to jello mixture.
Let cool, then add unsweetened pineapple juice and ReaLemon juice.
Freeze in plastic containers or paper milk cartons for several days prior to serving.

title: vanilla chip brownies
directions: Use 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs, gradually beating in sugar.
Blend in melted butter and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until brownies pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup (undiluted).
Dissolve cream cheese in heated soup (use electric beater).
Dissolve gelatin (as directed) in water. Add to soup mixture.
Add mayonnaise, green pepper, celery and onion.
Drain and rinse shrimp.
Add to mixture.
Mix and chill.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Let cool.
Shred (debone) chicken and mix with shredded cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Roll crescent rolls flat; put chicken mixture in the middle and roll up. Put in 13 x 9-inch dish (will use 2).
Mix cream of mushroom soup and 1 can milk.
Pour over chicken rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add rest of ingredients, except pecans.
Pour into deep pie shell.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: poor boy fillets
directions: Partially cook bacon and drain.
Combine all ingredients. Wrap with bacon; secure with wooden picks.
Grill over medium coals 8 minutes.
Turn and grill 8 minutes more.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken, debone and save broth.
Melt margarine and stir in dressing.
In greased 13 x 9-inch dish, put layer of dressing, layer of chicken, mushroom soup (diluted with broth).
Repeat using chicken soup (diluted with broth).
Top with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy refrigerator pickles
directions: Shake ingredients until dissolved.
Slice cucumbers into large jar and cover with mixture.
Place lid on jar and chill several hours or overnight.

title: grapefruit salad oriental
directions: Coarsely tear spinach into large salad bowl.
Add drained mushrooms, diced water chestnuts and diced grapefruit.
Mix oil, vinegar, grapefruit juice, soy sauce, liquid hot pepper sauce, salt and dry mustard.
Toss with spinach mixture.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: butter frosting
directions: Cream butter.
Add
remaining
ingredients and continue creaming until mixture is well blended and fluffy.
Will cover tops and sides of 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: squash cakes
directions: Combine squash and onions in a medium saucepan with salted water to cover.
Bring to a boil and cook 10 minutes, or until squash is tender, drain well.
Mash the squash and onion, and drain again.
Stir in eggs, salt, and pepper.

title: no-knead light rolls
directions: Combine water and yeast; let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Place butter, salt and sugar in separate bowl and pour hot water in and stir until dissolved.
When lukewarm, add yeast and beat in egg. Stir in flour and beat until blended to make soft dough.
Put dough in large greased bowl.
Either cover with foil and chill 2 to 12 hours or cover with cloth until doubled in bulk.
Punch down; shape rolls to fill muffin tins about 1/3.
Again, let rise until doubled.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: cornflake clusters
directions: This is simple and is great for dessert, breakfast, coffee breaks or snacks.

title: broccoli and cheese rice
directions: Cut up baked potatoes in small wedges.
Fry in bacon grease with onion, garlic salt, seasoned salt, salt and pepper to taste.

title: sherbet jello
directions: Note:
These ingredients should all be coordinating flavors such as raspberry jello, sherbet and fruit, orange jello, sherbet and fruit or lemon jello, sherbet and pineapple are all good combinations.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together all ingredients except 1/4 cup barbecue sauce.
Shape into loaf in 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Bake 45 minutes.
Top with remaining barbecue sauce.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: In large Dutch oven over high heat, heat a 2-inch depth of water to a boil; add eggplant, onion, pepper and zucchini.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until pepper and zucchini are tender-crisp.
Remove pepper and zucchini to plate to cool.
Cover Dutch oven; cook onion and eggplant for 10 to 15 minutes longer or until fork-tender.
Remove to plate to cool.
Cut zucchini, pepper and onion lengthwise in half; discard seeds from pepper.
Cut eggplant crosswise into 8 slices.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix berries, water and sugar.
Heat until sugar is dissolved and berries tender.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly in large bowl of electric mixer.
Add egg yolk, then flour sifted with cinnamon.
Pat into ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Pour unbeaten egg white over surface; drain off excess.
Sprinkle nuts over top, pressing them down lightly with flat of hand.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into bars while hot.
These freeze well.
Yields 3 dozen bars.

title: indian wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes in 9 x 13 pan.

title: strawberry almond parfait
directions: Combine sugar and water in a small saucepan; bring to a boil. Cook to soft ball stage or 238° on your candy thermometer.
Beat egg whites.
Pour the hot syrup over them in a thin stream and at same time, beat in almond extract.
Whip the cup of cream and fold into mixture.
Spoon alternate layers of mashed strawberries and cream mixture into parfait glasses.
Top with a whole, fresh strawberry.
Chill before serving.

title: mama's olive chicken and rice
directions: Boil rice in salted water for 20 minutes; drain.
While rice is cooking, put olive oil and water into pressure cooker; add seasoned chicken pieces, layering onion and olives between.
Cook at pressure 10 for around 15 to 18 minutes.
When the chicken is cooked, remove from pressure cooker, scraping onions and olives into the pot.
Add cooked rice to pot, stirring well to mix onion and olives and absorb juices.
Place chicken on top of rice, replace top of pressure cooker and cook an additional 1 to 2 minutes (before the top becomes locked on) to combine flavors. Then enjoy!

title: cinderella cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add oil; beat.
Add all dry ingredients; blend well.
Add pumpkin.
Pour into a 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Turn on rack and ice.

title: baptist delight
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Crust will be slightly browned. Combine next 3 ingredients and spread over cooled crust, using 1/2 of mixture. Save remaining mixture to be used in third layer. Hint: All the mixture can be used at this time, and just use Cool Whip on top layer. Combine next 3 ingredients until pudding begins to thicken. Pour over first layer. Spread remaining topping or Cool Whip over mixture. Decorate with shaved chocolate if desired.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients
in
blender;
mix for 3 minutes on low. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan; let sit for 5 minutes. Sprinkle 1 cup coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry goo
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water and cool.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar and add to Jell-O mixture.
Add vanilla and strawberries to Jell-O mixture.
Whip milk.
Fold into mixture. Pour into a thick graham cracker crust and chill overnight.

title: comfort soup
directions: Heat oil in soup pot.
Add mushrooms and stir-fry for two minutes.
Add noodles and stir-fry for one minute to heat through. Add boiling vegetable stock, tofu, spinach and scallions.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for one-half hour.
Serve with whole grain bread and tossed salad.

title: barbecue sauce(for spareribs or short ribs)
directions: Makes about 2 cups.
I usually boil the ribs about 30 to 60 minutes and then drain and put in slow cooker with sauce on top. Cook all day.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Add next 2 ingredients, mixing well.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until browned.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix broth with soup.
Cook noodles in broth.
Mix soups, butter and broth with spices and cheese.
Shred chicken.
Mix all together.
Spread in two (8 x 12-inch) pans.
Sprinkle with remainder of cheese.
Bake at 250° until cheese melts.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 of bread and 1/3 of grated cheese into greased casserole. Add ham & mushrooms. Top with remaining bread and cheese. Beat milk, eggs, & seasonings together and pour over mixture. Refrigerate over night. In morning, bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours uncovered. Serves 6.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix
sugar
and oil together.
Add well beaten eggs and mix well.
Sift
together dry ingredients.
Fold dry ingredients
into sugar, egg mixture.
Add carrots and pecans.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans
or
a
sheet
pan.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350° or until done.
Frost with Cream Cheese Maple Icing.

title: sparkling salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot applesauce.
Add pineapple and 7-Up. Mix well.
Put in mold and chill.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Prick pie crust with fork to make a crusty crust, then refrigerate.
In a small bowl beat egg substitute and flour.
Add sugar, pineapple juice, corn syrup, vanilla, salt and margarine to egg mixture.
Add nuts.
Place pie in a baking sheet and pour in filling.
Cook pie for 30 minutes at 350°, then reduce heat to 300° for 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Let pie cool on wire rack.

title: thick cake icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick; cool.
Cream together remaining ingredients; add custard to rest of ingredients.
Beat until well blended.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake 35 minutes longer, or until knife edge comes out clean.
Cool. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: sour cream sheet cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream thoroughly.
Add eggs and cocoa mixed with boiling water.
Add sour cream, flour and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost with fudge frosting.

title: individual shrimp quiche
directions: Cream butter and cheese very well; beat in 2 tablespoons cream; work in flour and salt to make dough.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: waffles
directions: Heat waffle iron while mixing batter.
Beat eggs well.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Bake until steaming stops.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well with wire whisk.
Set aside.

title: millionaire milk(a real crowd pleaser!)
directions: In a blender, combine low-fat milk, powdered milk and cocoa. Cover and blend at low speed for 10 seconds or until smooth. Pour into two glasses and enjoy!
Serves 2.

title: frijoles charros (bean soup)(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook beans, adding salt pork when done.
In skillet, saute next 6 ingredients.
Add to pot of beans when beans are done. (Keep beans a little juicy.)
Cover and let set for 1 hour for seasonings to set in.

title: marsala chicken in cream
directions: Combine 3 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken in mixture, shaking off excess.
Heat 4 tablespoons butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Brown chicken breasts on both sides. Stir in dry Marsala wine, chicken broth and tarragon.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until chicken is tender, about 15 minutes.
Remove breasts from skillet to a warm platter and keep warm.

title: cc's tuna bake
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine tuna, soup, milk, onions, celery, salt/pepper, and Mrs. Dash.
Stir until soup is smooth. Add to noodles along with peas.
Place in a greased casserole; top with dots of margarine or butter and sprinkle on bread crumbs.

title: rob's favorite quick baked beans]
directions: Fry 4 to 6 strips of bacon until crisp.
Add ketchup and mustard and stir to mix well.
Next add minced onion and cloves. Mix well.
Place beans in casserole.
Mix brown sugar through beans.
Add bacon mixture and stir until well mixed.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lemon loaf cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat 5 minutes (no more, no less). Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: melt in your mouth chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water and vanilla. Mix batter well, then add water and vanilla.
Put into floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in mixing bowl. Add shortening, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat for 2 minutes or until smooth.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by spoonful onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: thick batter for fried foods
directions: Blend dry ingredients in bowl.
Stir together eggs, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Prepare food to be fried.
Dry food thoroughly; coat with flour.
Using tongs, dip food into batter, letting excess drip off.
Heat oil in a deep fryer to 375°, deep enough to float food that is to be fried.
Fry until golden.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons of drippings in pan.
Set bacon aside.
Add potatoes, onion, carrots and celery to bacon drippings.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in milk and spices.
Bring to a boil. Stir together the sour cream, flour and paprika; gradually stir in about 1 cup of the hot mixture into sour cream mixture.
Return to remaining hot mixture in saucepan.
Cook and stir just until mixture bubbles.
Top with bacon pieces; serve immediately.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken, then broccoli in a 9 x 13 pan. Mix soup diluted with one can of milk, sour cream, mayo, onion, dash of Worcestershire and Tabasco sauce and a teaspoon of black pepper. Pour over broccoli. Prepare Stove Top dressing and cover top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered and uncovered for 15.

title: vegetable scramble
directions: Combine first five ingredients and cook with margarine in nonstick skillet.
Makes single serving along with 1 toasted English muffin with 2 teaspoons margarine.

title: coconut cake
directions: Punch holes in the end of the coconut and drain the milk (liquid).
Prepare cake mix as directed on box, but use the liquid from coconut instead of the water.
If needed, add some water to have the right amount of liquid.
Remove the brown skin from the coconut and pitch.
Grind or grate the white coconut meat.
Toast all of coconut lightly.
Mix desired amount into the cake batter and reserve some for the icing.
Bake as instructed on the cake box.

title: crab-shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole or individual crab shells.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix
listed
ingredients then fold in 18 ounces whipped topping.
Pour into 3 graham cracker pie crust shells.
Freeze and serve frozen.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Add juices and crushed fruits to sugar mixture.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw in refrigerator to mushy stage.
Mix with equal amounts of 7-Up or Sprite.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Bake at 325° using glass dish.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Use 2 level teaspoons for 1 cup of boiling water.
Add more sugar if wanted.

title: cheese ball dip
directions: Wash salt off beef and drain.
Soften cream cheese.
Chop meat and onions real fine.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Great with Ritz crackers.

title: coconut pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine flour and sugar; add salt, milk and egg yolks.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from the heat; stir in vanilla and 1 c coconut.
Pour hot filling into pie shell.
Spread meringue over hot filling.
Sprinkle remaining coconut over meringue.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes or until golden.
Cool.
Store in the refrigerator.
Serves 6-8.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Put all ingredients in
frying
pan
on medium heat and brown; set aside.
Put 1 (12
ounce) package black beans in 12 cups water.
Bring beans
and
water to a boil.
Reduce to low heat. Allow to simmer until beans are tender.
Place contents of frying pan
into
beans.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon olive oil and stir.
Serve over rice.

title: risi besi
directions: Heat oil and 2 tablespoons butter in large saucepan; saute onion for 5 minutes. Mix in rice and saute until clear. Add sherry and cook over low heat for 1 minute. Add broth, peas, salt and pepper. Cover and cook 15 minutes or until rice is tender. Remove from heat. Add cheese and remaining butter.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Place Jell-O in bowl with sugar.
Add boiling water; set aside.
Meanwhile, wash cranberries, then grind with meat grinder. Add to Jell-O mixture.
Add remaining ingredients, except marshmallows.
The marshmallows will go on top of mixture when you are finished mixing.
Place in refrigerator until serving time.

title: white almond fudge
directions: Lightly butter 8-inch square pan.
In medium saucepan, over very low heat, melt milk chips and condensed milk until smooth (stirring constantly).
Remove from heat and stir in toasted almonds and vanilla.
Spread in pan.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Makes 64 addicting pieces.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips and mix other ingredients.
Drop on wax paper.
Use your own judgement as to the size you want them.
(I use a scant teaspoonful for each cookie.)

title: sesame oven fried chicken
directions: Combine egg and milk.

Mix dry ingredients in a paper bag. Dip chicken in egg mixture, then shake in paper bag. Place chicken in a 14 x 9-inch baking dish, skin side up. Pour melted butter or margarine over chicken and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: holiday thumbprints
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well, then add 2 1/4 cups of all-purpose flour.
Roll out and cut with favorite cookie cutters. Bake at 350° to 375° until golden brown.
Great cookie recipe for the holidays.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Cook in crock-pot on high for 3 hours, covered. Remove lid and cook for 5 hours, uncovered. Pour into sterile jars and seal.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and cream.
Mix until smooth.
Cook until bubbly and slightly thickened.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk, 1/4 cup of butter and vanilla together. Top with brown sugar, 3/4 cup butter, coconut and pecans.
Spread and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate covered easter eggs
directions: Melt margarine. Add peanut butter.
Add sugar.
Use hands to mix well.
Mold into egg shapes.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Dip frozen candy into melted chocolate and put on waxed paper to harden.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: salmon dip
directions: Stir well to blend.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish with red peppers and serve with an assortment of crackers.

title: blueberry kuchen
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, salt and 2 tablespoons granulated sugar. Work in butter with fingers.
Mix in vinegar.
Spread this crust mixture into a 9-inch pan.
Make it 1/4-inch deep and go around sides to 1-inch height.
Combine 1 cup granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and cinnamon. Add 2 cups blueberries.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: jack-o-lantern cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
To form cookie, drop dough by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet, spreading into pumpkin shape.
Add a little dough to form stem.
Bake until lightly brown, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheets to cool.
Decorate using icing, candies, raisins, nuts, etc.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix well and put in a pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour and butter together until they form small crumbs. Stir in pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple whiskey pie
directions: Beat hot apples with sugar and butter.
When slightly cooled, add whiskey, cream, nutmeg and beaten egg yolks.
Add beaten whites last and more whiskey if you wish.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan (no upper crust); bake at 425° for 10 minutes to set crust.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes longer. Decorate cooled pie with sweetened whipped cream.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Slice apples thin to dip.

title: cheddar-potato bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, sour cream, onion and pepper.
Stir in potatoes until blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until hot and bubbling.

title: chow chows
directions: Boil vinegar and sugar for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Put all vegetables through a coarse food chopper (processor).
Add salt to vegetables; mix well and let stand for 4 hours.
Squeeze all the juice out, then add cooled vinegar.
Put in prepared jars and seal.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins.
Cool and peel into thin slices. In a saucepan over low heat, combine Cheddar cheese and butter. Stir until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, green onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in the potatoes and turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 450° oven for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add milk.
Pour pineapple over cubed bread.
Add creamed mixture.
Stir slightly.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Great as a side dish with baked ham.

title: stuffed peppers(ultra low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef in large skillet; pour off grease, if any.
Add tomatoes, water, Italian seasoning and salt.
Bring to boil.
Stir in instant rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes or until rice has absorbed liquid.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 1 inch apart.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 7 dozen cookies.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat.
Add oregano, pepper, bread crumbs, tomato sauce and onion.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Beat egg in milk.
Stir in cheese.
Put on top of meat mixture.
Bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: homemade sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes to soup stage.
Chop or grind the onions and hot peppers.
Add to tomatoes and cook for 1 hour.
Add tomato paste, oil, oregano, basil, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil.
Pack into jars and seal.
Makes 10 quarts.

title: apricot-coconut balls
directions: Combine apricots and coconut.
Add milk and mix well.
Shape into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Let stand 2 hours. Makes 5 dozen.

title: double-good texas peanut clusters
directions: Place chocolate chips in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-proof bowl. Microwave on Medium power for 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Fold in peanut butter and shortening.
Microwave on High power for 1 minute or until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Stir in peanuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet lined with waxed paper. Chill until set; store in refrigerator.
Yield: 12 clusters.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add vanilla, flour, salt, baking powder and nuts.
Spread evenly in an 8 x 8-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake for about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chili rellenos(mexican)
directions: Rinse chilies; pat dry with paper towel.
Carefully remove seeds.
Insert cheese strips into chilies.
Roll in flour.
Beat egg whites in small bowl with electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Beat yolks in another small bowl until fluffy and pale yellow, about 5 minutes.
Beat in flour, yeast, water and salt. Gently fold in beaten whites.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter; mix with dressing.
Beat egg slightly.
Mix remaining ingredients all together until well blended.
Put into greased casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a large pot combine chicken broth, water, potatoes, carrots, celery and onions.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add broccoli and cauliflower and cook for ten minutes longer.
Add cream of chicken soup and cheese until cheese melts.

title: chocolate plunge
directions: Bring syrup and cream to boil in microwave.
Add chocolate. Stir until melted.
Serve as dip for fruit.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix
sugar,
cocoa,
margarine	and
milk
in saucepan; bring to	rolling boil.
Boil for 2 minutes; remove from heat. Quickly stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon by the teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Add dough to make soft dough.
Place on floured surface and knead lightly a few seconds, using as little flour as possible.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 450° for about 12 minutes.

title: layered chili powder salad
directions: Drain chilies.
Shred lettuce.
Cube cheese.
Cut beef into strips.
Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Peel and chop avocado. Combine mayonnaise, chilies, milk, chili powder and salt; mix well.
Chill.
On serving platter, arrange lettuce, meat, cheese, tomatoes, avocado and olives.
Serve with mixture and chips.

title: four fold delight
directions: Mix together.
Press into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool and add 2nd layer.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and onion in large bowl.
Just before serving add beans, toss well and serve chilled.

title: potatoes dumplings
directions: Slice bacon into cubes and fry.
Drain off grease and set aside.
Put grease back into frying pan and add potatoes.
When potatoes are done, add eggs.
While potatoes are frying, make your sauce.
Place bacon, milk, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Simmer on low heat about 1 hour.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour until combined. Add cream and 1 1/2 cups broth.
Cook and stir until bubbly, then cook 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat; add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in rest of ingredients, adding additional broth if needed.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Marinate your favorite choice of meat for at least 4 hours. Turn occasionally and pierce meat to ensure deep marination. Charcoal or broil, brushing marinade generously on both sides while cooking.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar well.
Add and mix eggs, flour, vanilla, salt and baking soda.
Gently stir in nuts, apples, raisins and coconut.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Pour cake in pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Combine
chicken
and onion and refrigerate for several hours. Add
celery, almonds, grapes, oranges, cooked macaroni and salad
dressing.
Refrigerate.
Just
before
serving, combine the whipping cream with the powdered sugar;
whip and blend this into the salad.
Serves 8.

title: biscuits
directions: Put all together in bowl and blend with pie dough blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork. Turn out on lightly floured board.
Mix with a little flour.
Use hands to mix or turn 6 times.
Pat out with hands 1/2-inch thick and cut biscuits with a cutter.
Bake about 20 minutes or until brown in 450° oven.

title: oysters a-la-henry
directions: Place oysters on shallow Pyrex or foiled dish (sprayed or greased).
Sprinkle on all dry ingredients, then put a pat of butter and sprinkle Worcestershire sauce on top of each oyster. Bake in oven until oysters curl and crumbs are brown at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sunday brunch
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
On each slice of bread in a baking dish, put one piece of ham or bacon, slices of sharp Cheddar cheese and top with another slice of bread.
Mix the eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard together.
Into this mixture, pour the green pepper and chopped onions.
Pour egg mixture over bread and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, melt butter and mix it with crushed potato chips.
Sprinkle the buttered chips over the bread and bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook, pick and dice the chicken and place in casserole dish. Blend soups and sour cream together and spread over diced chicken. Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle over chicken mixture as topping. Brown in 350° oven about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Follow directions to cook broccoli.
Place cooked broccoli in casserole dish.
Combine soup and milk and pour mixture over broccoli.
Place cheese slices over broccoli to completely cover it.
Crush crackers and combine with butter or margarine; fold this together until mixed thoroughly.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over cheese to cover complete dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: bologna casserole
directions: Place potatoes in casserole.
Cover with bologna.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over bologna.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° about an hour.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Combine all nuts.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to full boil.
Lower heat and boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanuts.
Beat until thickens (about 5 minutes).
Drop quickly by teaspoon on waxed paper to form clusters.
Makes 24.

title: nut loaf
directions: Let stand for 20 minutes before baking.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Place raw chicken in casserole. Salt and pepper. Add other ingredients over top. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill until ready to serve.

title: brennan's best meatloaf
directions: In saucepan, medium heat. put ketchup, water, salt, pepper, onions, sugar, worcestershire sauce, and mustard mix well and simmer. In large bowl mix beef, crackers, egg, onion, and milk. Mixing gently.
Place in loaf pan. Poke holes with your finger along the top approx. 1 inch apart.
(make sure you have formed a loaf by loosening from the side of the pan).
Pour sauce which you have been simmering over meatloaf.
Bake at 325° for 1 1\2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken breast into strips and bake in greased pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Mix eggs and soups together.
Add peas and cubed bread.
Put dressing mix on chicken and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry french toast
directions: In a shallow bowl, beat together the eggs and milk; set aside. Spread 1 tablespoon of preserves on 8 slices of bread.
Top each with remaining bread, pressing together lightly.
Dip filled bread into egg mixture, coating both sides.
In a skillet or on a griddle, cook bread in hot margarine or butter over medium heat about 2 minutes on each side.
Add more butter or margarine as needed.
Serve with fruit-flavored syrup.

title: chicken livers with noodles
directions: Wash the livers and cut into small pieces; then fry in the oil, butter and the 1/2 onion.
Take the onion out when pale golden color.
Cook the livers on high for a few minutes; then reduce and cover.
Remove the tomato skins and take out the seeds.
Cut them into pieces; add to the livers.
Add salt and pepper; simmer.
Cook the noodles; add a pinch of soda.
When ready, drain and place on a serving platter.
Pour the liver mixture all over the spaghetti, knobs of butter and the Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: chicken poulet
directions: Mix stuffing mix, margarine and broth together lightly. Add veggies, mayonnaise and salt. Mix well and press mixture into a greased 12 x 8 baking dish. Beat eggs and milk together. Pour over top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: red salad dressing
directions: Mix well and refrigerate in a quart jar. Keeps a long time.

title: cranberry pecan salad
directions: Soak gelatin in small amount of cold water.
Add soaked gelatin and Jell-O to 2 cups boiling water.
Let cool and partly congeal, then add other ingredients.
Pour into molds.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Combine 1/4 cup corn syrup, brown sugar and margarine in medium size saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture begins to boil. Remove from heat. Add rice crispy cereal, stirring until well coated.
Press evenly in 9-inch pie to form crust. Put in freezer until crust is firm.

title: layered hamburg bake
directions: Cook noodles 10 minutes; drain.
Brown meat and drain.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, salts, pepper and cooked noodles.
Set aside. Stir cream cheese, sour cream, milk and onions.
In 2-quart casserole, layer 1/2 of ground beef and noodles and 1/2 cream cheese mixture.
Add all spinach, then remaining beef and noodles. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and spread remaining cream cheese on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 additional minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crumbs and 1/2 cup butter in a bowl. Mix well and spread and pat in bottom of an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch shallow baking dish.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together until moist the margarine and graham crackers. Spread 2/3 of this mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
The rest is used for topping.

title: pineapple loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add
eggs
1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and lemon juice. Stir in flour and mix well.
Add
pineapple
(be
sure that all juice has been drained).
Spoon batter into a greased and floured tube pan or a loaf pan.
Bake
at
for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
No
frosting
is	needed	for this cake;	it keeps well.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator (covered).

title: apple barn fresh apple cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and sugar.
Mix in oil, eggs, vanilla and apples.
Bake at 325° in tube pan for 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Boil turkey tails, necks and giblets until tender.
Remove meat from bones of tails and necks.
Chop giblets.
Bake large pan of regular corn bread (no sugar).
Cool and crumble.
Combine all ingredients.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Layer the cereal, nuts and pretzels in pan.
Heat remaining ingredients and pour over cereal.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine butter and flour in a small saucepan over low heat. Blend until smooth.
Gradually stir milk into flour mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese and salt, stirring until cheese melts.
Place asparagus in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Add cheese sauce.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: lana's hershey bar cake
directions: Mix as directed per back of cake mix box.
Use two 9 inch cake pans or three 8 inch cake pans.

title: ann's chinese walnut chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add walnuts, stirring constantly until toasted.
Remove nuts and drain on paper towels.
Put chicken in hot oil; sprinkle with salt.
Cook on high heat until no pink remains.
Remove.
Add onion, celery and 1/2 cup chicken broth; cook 5 minutes or until tender.

title: baked lemon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Clean chicken and remove all fat.
Drain and wipe dry with paper towels.
Roll lemons on counter to soften. Wash in warm water and roll again.
Prick each lemon about 20 times with toothpick.
Place lemons in cavity of chicken.
Close cavity; also tie legs close to body.
Press ground pepper into chicken on all surfaces.
Place chicken breast side down in roasting pan and place in upper 1/3 of oven.
Bake about 15 minutes.
Chicken will baste itself.
Turn chicken breast side up and bake another 20 minutes (approximately).
Turn oven to 400°.
Bake 15 minutes more. Chicken will be beautifully brown and puffed up.
Remove lemons before carving.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil and cook, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and let cool about 30 minutes.

title: impossible taco salad
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir beef and onion until browned.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix.
Spread in plate.
Top with chilies.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth (1 minute).
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes. Top with sour cream, shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix together well.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot soup
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and saute carrots and onions for 5 minutes until soft, but not browned.
Add broth and bay leaf. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool. Remove bay leaf.
Puree in blender until smooth.
Stir in orange juice and chill.
Just before serving, stir in cream and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: popsicles
directions: Using any flavor of jello and Kool-Aid, mix together.
Add 2 cups boiling water; mix until dissolved.
Add 2 cups cold water. Pour into popsicle containers or ice cube trays.

title: easy barbecue sauce for hots, hamburgs, ribs
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Simmer until onion is cooked.

title: processor french bread
directions: Mix flour, yeast, salt and sugar into work bowl.
Press on/off on processor to blend.
Add water through feed tube, a ball will form.
Knead for 1 minute in processor.
Place in greased bowl. Turn dough over and let rise until double in bowl.
Punch down and shape into 2 baguettes.
Place in greased baguette pans and rise until doubled.
Slash tops with razor and bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes with pan of water in the oven if you want true French bread texture.
Remove water, brush with salt water and bake 10 minutes more.
Cool on wire racks.

title: american style enchiladas
directions: In saucepan, heat cream of mushroom soup and green chilies over low heat.
While simmering, brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Roll ground beef and beans, if desired, into tortilla shells.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over all. Completely cover with grated cheese.
Decorate with sliced black olives.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with lettuce, taco sauce, etc.

title: spanish cream(dessert)
directions: Soak gelatine in milk in top of double boiler for 5 minutes. Add sugar and salt.
Place over boiling water until gelatine is dissolved.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks slightly and add milk mixture to yolks, beating with fork to mix.
Return to double boiler and cook until slightly thickened.
Fold into egg whites, beaten until stiff, but not dry.
Refrigerate until set.
Best if allowed to mellow for a day.

title: chocolate goody
directions: Melt all chocolate together in a double boiler.
Add water and sugar a little at a time until all is combined.
Let cool.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Let chocolate mixture come to room temperature and fold in beaten egg whites. Layer dish on the bottom with macaroons and lady fingers around the side.
Pour in chocolate mixture.
Refrigerate.
Whip heavy cream until stiff.
Spread over top of chocolate mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pickled turnips
directions: Peel turnips.
Cut crosswise in thin slices, not more than 1/4-inch thick. Mix with salt.
Let stand 1 hour. Drain
and rinse thoroughly with water.
Bring to a boil vinegar, sugar, food coloring and paprika.
Add turnips and simmer 2 minutes; cool.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix sugar, water, cinnamon and cloves in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Add tea and heat through. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Strain and add remaining ingredients. Heat but do not boil.
Serve hot.
Makes about 8 measuring cups.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Heat oven to 350°, put in Bundt or tube pan that has been greased, bake one hour.

title: hearty ham and cheese chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add the ham.
Stir together the flour and small amounts of milk (gradually, to prevent lumps).
Add to onion and ham.
Stir in potatoes and seasonings; stir until thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Serves 8.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In large skillet, cook chicken and red or green pepper in margarine until pepper is tender.
Stir together flour, bouillon, pepper, milk and 1 cup of water.
Add to the skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese, spaghetti and mushrooms.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until heated through.

title: grandma bennett's nut wafer cookies(born 1895 and still going)
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs slowly, mixing thoroughly.
Add nuts and then dry ingredients.
Shape into 1 foot rolls (like shaping long thin meat loaf).
Put in icebox overnight.
When ready to bake, slice in 1/4-inch pieces.
Bake in a 375° oven for approximately 10 to 15 minutes or until brown on bottoms.
These will be very crunchy when cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes on low heat.
Great on chicken, pork chops and venison.

title: norwegian lamb and cabbage
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces; put them in large saucepan.
Add water; cover.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 1 hour.
Remove meat from pan; set aside.
Leave liquid in pan.
Layer meat and cabbage in same pan while you sprinkle each layer with flour and salt. Put pepper bag into kettle.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with boiled potatoes and cranberry sauce.

title: cole slaw & noodles salad
directions: Mix 2 pkgs. of flavoring from noodles with sugar and oil.
Mix well and set aside.

title: ground beef on rye
directions: Saute meats and pepper flakes until brown.
Drain.
Turn to simmer and add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add seasoning.
Spread on cocktail rye.
Place on cookie sheets and freeze, then store in freezer Ziploc bags.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine in food processor. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy strawberry trifle
directions: Place layers of cake, strawberry Jell-O mixture, pudding mixture and Cool Whip in large bowl; repeat layers, topping with Cool Whip.
Make several hours ahead or night before.
Delicious light dessert if made with low-fat milk and light Cool Whip.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on cake box in a 9 x 13-inch pan; let cool.
Spread on top of cooled cake in order:
Eagle Brand milk, pineapple (do not drain), Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine undiluted soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt.
Add turkey, rice, eggs, celery, water chestnuts and onions.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Mix in almonds.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Add sugar, beat well; add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add sifted flour and beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat until very fluffy.
Spoon into buttered and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving juice. Slice bananas into pineapple juice and let set for 2 to 3 minutes to help keep from turning brown. Drain oranges and bananas.
Mix all ingredients, adding pie filling last. This is good as a salad or topping for cake!

title: peas in tomato sauce
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, brown the meat over high heat.
After browned, reduce heat and braise for about 1 hour adding a little water as needed.
Add diced onions, stir and cook until translucent.
Add salt, pepper and tomato sauce along with the juice from the peas (or beans).
Cover, reduce heat and let simmer for approximately one hour until sauce thickens.
Add peas or beans and just heat through.
Serve immediately over rice.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cut in small pieces, pineapple, cherries and dates.
Sprinkle 1 cup plain flour over fruit.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add other flour and beat eggs, cinnamon and soda.
Pour on fruit.
Mix by hand.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Don't cover for at least 3 hours after baking.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix together liquids and pour over chicken in baking pan. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk. Microwave on high for approx. 6 minutes, stirring often. When mixture starts to thicken, beat the egg yolks and add some of the hot mixture to them. Stir and slowly add this to the rest of the mixture. Microwave 1 more minute. Check for thickening consistency. Remove, add butter and vanilla. Pour into pie shell. Use egg whites to make meringue. Brown top in oven.

title: egg nog
directions: Mix all together, you have egg nog.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chew bread 2
directions: Blend brown sugar and eggs.
Melt margarine and mix with brown sugar mixture. Blend in flour, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until sugar is dissolved and it just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Add cornflakes and stir until mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or foil.

title: ready to eat pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt over cucumbers, green pepper and onions.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Do not drain.
Mix sugar, celery seed and vinegar.
Stir this mixture occasionally during the time cucumbers are standing.
At the end of 2 hours, sugar will be dissolved. Pour cold syrup over vegetables and refrigerate in a covered container.
They can be eaten when chilled.
They keep for weeks.

title: hot tamales
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixer.
Pour into meat mixture after blended.

title: saba mama
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add ice, if desired.

title: rice and beans
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic with smoked sausage.
Add water and rice; cook 20 minutes or until rice is done.
Add beans and tomatoes.
Good as a vegetable dish with sausage left out.

title: autumn chutney
directions: Peel and chop apples and pears.
Begin cooking them in large saucepan in cider and lemon juice, stirring frequently.
Add sugar and spices as juices come from fruit.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, stirring frequently, at gentle bubble, until moisture cooks off and mixture thickens.
Keeps well for several weeks in the refrigerator.
Freeze or can for longer storage.
Serve warm as a side dish or garnish for beef, ham or pork.
Also makes a good stuffing for pork chops.

title: peter paul cake
directions: Fix cake mix according to directions and let cool. Cut the layers in half with a string and set aside.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Beat eggs whites until stiff, then fold into cake mixture.
Beat well.
Pour in greased tube pan. Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°
or until done when tested. Cool before slicing.

title: marinade for london broil
directions: Poke holes in meat with kitchen fork.
Marinade for 6 to 24 hours.
The longer the better.
Poke more holes in the meat and turn.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: double berry punch
directions: In a large container, combine cranberry-raspberry drink, lemon juice and sugar.
Stir well until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Just before serving, add raspberries and carbonated beverage.
Serve over ice.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: ambrosia pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, orange rind, butter and vanilla in blender.
Pour into greased or buttered 9-inch pie dish or pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tasty potato and vegetable casserole
directions: Toss carrots, onions and potatoes with dressing.
Bake in a casserole for 1 hour or until tender, stirring occasionally, at 400°.
Very easy.
Very tasty!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, egg, salt and pepper in bowl.
Stir in shredded cheese. Add macaroni.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and drain strawberries.
Bake pie crust, cool and fill with strawberries.
Bring the sugar, cornstarch and water to a boil.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Allow the mixture to cool and pour over strawberries.
Refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: potato topped meat loaf
directions: Measure 1/4 cup gravy from jar and combine with beef and next 5 ingredients. Form into a loaf (8 x 4 x 1 1/2-inch) in a shallow baking pan. Bake in 350° oven 1 hour. Remove from oven and carefully drain fat. Spread hot mashed potatoes over top and sides of meat loaf. Drizzle melted butter over top of potatoes. Garnish with gravy and paprika.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add and beat into mixture one egg at a time.
Mix in creamed corn, peppers, cheese and milk.
Sift dry ingredients into mixture.
Mix just enough to blend well.
Turn into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 40 minutes in preheated oven at 325°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In skillet, lightly brown meat with onion and seasonings; drain off fat.
Set aside.

In buttered casserole (2 to 2 1/2-quart), cut cabbage in medium size shreds to cover bottom of dish. Add about 4 layers of sliced potatoes (about 6 medium size). Arrange the browned meat over the potatoes.
Pour tomato juice over the meat.
Cover and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven. Serves 6.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix altogether and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: mandel bread(dessert)
directions: Blend oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients gradually into batter.
Add nuts and chips.
Mix by hand.
Moisten hands with oil and roll into 4 rolls. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Slice after removing from oven.

title: chicken margarita salad
directions: Marinate chicken at least 2 hours in pineapple juice, brown sugar and soy sauce mixture.
Place chicken on grill and cook for 8 minutes on each side.
Brush with marinade.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and brush with Margarita Butter.
Serve chicken on mixed greens, topped with shredded Co-Jack cheese, tomato wedges, croutons and choice of dressing.
Serves 2.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; toss.

title: maid rites
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Add remaining ingredients in pan. Cook on low about 30 minutes.
Serve with hamburger buns.

title: candied carrots
directions: Set out small baking dish.
Wash carrots and pare or scrape (peel).
Cook whole carrots 15 to 25 minutes or until just tender. Meanwhile, combine brown sugar, water and butter or margarine in a small saucepan.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Drain carrots and place in baking dish.
Cover with sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until carrots are completely glazed; baste occasionally.
Takes 30 minutes, yields 6 servings.

title: spicy pumpkin cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Coat 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans with cooking spray.

title: london broil strips
directions: Combine egg and milk.
Cut London broil into 1/4 inch strips. Dip London broil into egg and milk mixture, then into bread crumbs and fry in butter approximately 5 minutes on each side.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil in salted water until done but not overcooked.
Drain almost all of water and let cool.
Dice onion, green pepper and eggs.
Mix all with pickle cubes, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar and black pepper.
Let stand until potatoes cool.
Mix all together.
Pour on serving platter and sprinkle top with paprika.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in 2 cups of water until done.
Remove chicken from water and cube.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Cook until done in water that chicken was cooked in.
Add vegetables to potatoes and cook until tender.
Add soup and chicken.
Mix well.
Put in pie shell and place second pie shell on top.
Bake until golden brown (approximately 30 minutes).

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix and beat 6 minutes on medium speed.
Bake in Bundt cake pan at 350°, approximately 50 minutes.

title: mom's karo nut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream flour, butter and sugar.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add Karo.
(I use a little more than 3/4 cup white with enough dark to finish out the cup.)
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix only enough to blend ingredients.
Pour into crust. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° and continue baking until pie is almost firm.
It will still shake slightly in the center.
(This is approximately 30 minutes.)

title: corn-on-the-cob
directions: Place corn in boiling water.
Add salt.
Boil corn for 30 minutes.
Remove corn; add butter and salt to taste.
Serves 2.

title: strawberry trifle(a country thanksgiving at the lamars)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a saucepan, heat milk and butter until butter melts.
Keep hot.
Beat eggs at high speed of mixer until thick and lemon-colored, about 3 minutes. Gradually add sugar, beating constantly for 4-5 minutes.
Add dry ingredients and stir until just blended.
Stir in hot mild and vanilla.
Blend well.
Divide batter between 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until done. Cool in pans 10 minutes.

title: tom yam goong(hot and spicy shrimp soup)
directions: Heat chicken stock over high heat, bring to a boil.
Add the Tom Yam Goong paste, lemon grass sprig and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low, simmer and cover for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp and mushrooms and cook for 2 minutes.
Do not overcook shrimp.
Add lime juice and garnish with coriander sprigs.
Serve immediately.

title: easy peach or apple crisp
directions: Pour fruit with juices into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season apples with cinnamon, sugar and ginger.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: dried apple stack cake
directions: Cream sugar
and shortening;
add molasses, vanilla and eggs and
beat
thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately
with
milk to creamed mixture.
Divide batter into 6 equal
parts
and
shape
into round balls.
Place each ball in the
middle
of a greased and floured 9-inch cake pan. Pat dough to edge
of pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. Cool layers slightly,
about
minutes and remove from pan. Spread hot filling
on
top
of each layer.
Let cake ripen in closed container for 10 to 12 hours before serving.

title: quick butter fluff rolls
directions: Soak yeast in warm water 5 minutes.
Combine buttermilk, sugar, salt, soda, shortening, eggs, yeast mixture and half of flour in mixing bowl.

title: spinach broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach and broccoli as directed on package. Mix with cheese, melted butter, salt and pepper.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with fresh bread crumbs, which have been tossed in 1/4 cup butter and sage.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Mix in pan salt, pepper, catsup, onions, chili pepper or powder and tomato paste.
Bring to boil, add raw hamburger, simmer for 4 hours.
Add water if you want thinner.
If you don't want to make that much, use 1/2 of everything but, don't forget you can always freeze it.

title: oven baked rosemary potato chips
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Brush 2 large cookie sheets with 1 teaspoon oil. Arrange potato slices in one flat layer. Brush potatoes with remaining oil and bake until golden brown. Check often since they brown at different rates, about 15 to 20 minutes. Transfer to paper towel and sprinkle with rosemary and salt while hot. Makes 4 servings. Prep time: 10 minutes. Cooking time: 20 minutes.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until edges are golden brown.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Melt butter in heavy baking dish.
Stir in salt.
Add pecans and toss well until thoroughly coated.
Add Worcestershire, cayenne pepper, cinnamon and Tabasco.
Toss again. Roast in oven 45 minutes, stirring frequently until nuts are crisp.
Turn off oven and leave in closed oven for another 1/2 hour.
Makes 4 cups.
These will keep or freeze.

title: chocolate peanut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Reserve 1/3 cup of the frosting in large bowl.
Combine remaining frosting, peanut butter and egg; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour in measuring cup.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheets.
Flatten each into 2-inch circle with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 4 to 7 minutes or until set.
Do not overbake.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheets.
Cool completely.
Lightly frost with reserved 1/3 cup frosting.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour.
Saute in butter until golden brown. Mix soup, onion and seasonings in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour rice into shallow 2-quart casserole.
Stir all except 1/3 cup soup mixture into rice.
Top with chicken.
Pour on remaining soup mixture. Cover.
Bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: mexican salad
directions: Saute meat and onion.
When meat is brown, add taco mix as directed.

title: dream dessert
directions: Fix jello as directed, adding 1/2 cup sugar. Let set until the consistency of jelly, then whip and fold in drained pineapple. Whip cream and fold into mixture. Put in 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate.
This can be served plain or on a lettuce leaf. The juice from the pineapple can be used in making the jello.

title: reception style cheese biscuits
directions: Cream the cheese and butter together (must be at room temperature).
Mix remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls or cut like biscuits.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: grilled salmon steaks
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Place fish in a shallow dish or large glass pie plate.
(Note: metal pie tin may not react well with the lemon juice for 6 hours.)

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix meat together with the rice, water, egg, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Melt 2 tablespoons shortening in skillet.
Shape meat balls.
Brown in skillet; stir together other ingredients. Pour over meat balls.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 45 minutes or until done.
If necessary, add water while cooking.

title: old-fashioned teacakes
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, milk and dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Place dough on a lightly floured board.
Sprinkle a little flour over the dough and roll to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in a moderate oven at 350° or 375° for about 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
This recipe does not call for pecans, but I add 1 cup chopped.
It makes them better.

title: purple cow
directions: Blend both ingredients to taste in blender until milkshake consistency.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cook pumpkin and drain.
Then add ingredients; beat until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Makes 3 pies.

title: "outside in" burgers
directions: Mix meat with the salt, pepper and parsley.
Divide into 8 portions.
Flatten each portion to make rounds 4 to 5 inches in diameter.
Top 4 patties with onion, tomato and cheese.
Top 4 patties with mustard, relish and mayonnaise.
Place relish patties over other patties, carefully enclosing all the relishes on the inside.
Press out any air bubbles and seal well.
Broil or grill about 4 minutes on each side.
Top with lettuce and place into prepared buns.
Serve immediately.

title: sugarless raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water, bring to a boil.
Add oil, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Let cool.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a separate bowl.
Beat eggs in separate bowl, then add to cooled raisin mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
(I use whole wheat flour.) Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean. (If mixture seems too wet, add a little more flour.)

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix lime jello with regular amount of water.
Pour into large rectangular Pyrex dish and allow to set.
Mix 1 cup hot water with lemon jello and dissolve.
Add marshmallows and cream cheese. Melt thoroughly.

title: spiders
directions: Melt morsels in double boiler.
When melted, add noodles and peanuts.
Mix well and drop by tablespoons on wax paper.
Chill to set.

title: red devils
directions: Soften cheese. Blend in ham. Refrigerate until firm. Shape into about 30 small balls. Roll in finely chopped nuts. Refrigerate until serving time. Serve on toothpicks. Makes about 30 balls.

title: chocolate banana peanut butter snack
directions: Peel bananas; slice in half.
Place in bowl in an "X" design. Put chocolate between each banana slice and peanut butter in the center of the bowl.
Dip banana in chocolate and/or peanut butter, then eat!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes, then uncover for 40 minutes.
Stir again before serving.

title: brandied yams
directions: Cook unpared sweet potatoes in boiling, salted water for 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool.
In saucepan, mix cornstarch, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Stir in water.
Cook over low heat until sauce is clear.
Stir in lemon juice and brandy. Peel potatoes and slice crosswise 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Put slices into a buttered 9-inch square baking dish.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: sylvia's country style chicken
directions: In 12-inch skillet, brown chicken in oil and butter; remove to plate.
To drippings in skillet, add potatoes and apples; cook, stirring, until browned.
With slotted spoon, remove to bowl.
To skillet, add onion; cook, stirring, until browned.
Return chicken to skillet and add next 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Return potatoes to skillet; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Return apples to skillet; cover and simmer 10 minutes until all are tender. Arrange on platter.
Skim fat from liquid in skillet.
Stir together water and flour; add to skillet.
Cook, stirring, over low heat until mixture boils and thickens; spoon over chicken.

title: lemon-pineapple banana dessert
directions: Mix lemon Jell-O according to package directions.
When set, mix lemon pudding.
Slice bananas (crosswise).
Place over Jell-O mixture.
Immediately cover with pudding mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Dredge pork chops in flour; brown on both sides in oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Drain on paper towels.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of drippings in skillet.
Saute onion and bell pepper in hot drippings until tender.
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Return pork chops to skillet.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until pork chops are tender.
Serve over rice. Yields 6 servings.

title: extra-easy lasagna
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef until browned, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce; heat through, stirring occasionally.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish, spread 1 1/2 cups meat mixture.
Top with three uncooked lasagna noodles, half of the Ricotta cheese and half of the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Slowly pour water around inside edges of baking dish. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Garnish each serving with salad greens and tomatoes, if desired. Makes 8 main dish servings.
Preparation Time: 10 minutes.
Cook Time:
65 minutes.
Stand Time:
10 minutes.

title: bing cherry butter
directions: Combine both ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Mix until blended and smooth.
Store in refrigerator.

title: summer sandwiches
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise. Scoop avocado out and mash well with a fork. Squeeze lime juice into avocado, mash a little more. Spread avocado on bread. Place sliced garlic here and there. Top with red onion, cheese and tomatoes. Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until cheese is melted well. Serves 4.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken; soak tortillas in 1 cup broth until soft.
Place tortillas in bottom of casserole dish.
Place a layer of chicken, a layer of cheese, onion and pepper on tortillas. Pour soup over top.
Add tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Prepare cake batter using the box instructions.
For more of a pineapple flavor, use the juice from the pineapple can instead of water.
Cover the entire bottom of an electric skillet with 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Turn to 250° and melt the margarine. Spread the brown sugar over the margarine.
Place the pineapple slices in the skillet.
Place a cherry in the center of each slice.
Pour batter of cake on top of the pineapple.
Place the cover on the skillet with the vent open.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes. The cake will look moist and uneven.
Turn onto serving plate. Slowly peel off wax paper.

title: no bake cookies #2
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, salt and oleo 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: potatoes erin
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Squeeze margarine on cut side of potato to cover top.
Sprinkle paprika, chili powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Place cut side down on pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Stir-fry chicken in hot oil in a large skillet until brown. Add vegetables, stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Mix broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar, garlic and ginger.
Add to skillet. Bring to boil and boil 1 minute.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix with other ingredients. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls.
May be frozen.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 20 minutes or 25 minutes if frozen.

title: cherry crumble
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in a cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: party shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into a ball.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: crispy hush puppies
directions: Mix well.
Gradually add 1 cup tap water and thoroughly mix all ingredients.
